-- Chapter 117 — ℚ is a FULLY VERIFIED FIELD: the GENERAL multiplicative inverse on
-- ANY nonzero rational (telos-3 / M6 numeric tower).  ch116 landed the ℤ zero-test
-- `zIsZero`/`zNonzero` (the decidability prerequisite); ch113 proved the inverse on the
-- POSITIVE subtype only.  This chapter CLOSES the gap: the inverse of a/sb is sb/a, whose
-- denominator `a : Z` has ARBITRARY sign — it needs SIGN NORMALISATION to keep the
-- denominator positive.  The whole ch116 development (ch07/ch103/ch105/ch107/ch108/ch113
-- ℤ+ℚ + the zIsZero discriminator) is redeclared VERBATIM below (self-contained); the NEW
-- layer begins under the "CHAPTER 117" banner at the very end.
--
-- LANDS in the NEW (ch117) layer, FULLY PROVEN, no admits/holes/postulates:
--   • monus (truncated Nat subtraction) + its laws: monusSuccSucc, monusZeroL,
--     monusShift (monus (a+c)(b+c) = monus a b) — the magnitude algebra.
--   • zMag : Z -> Nat — the absolute value |m−n| of a rep (m,n), as add (monus m n)
--     (monus n m) (at most one summand is nonzero). The CRUX `zMagRespects` ((m,n)~(c,d)
--     ⟹ zMag = zMag) via monusShift + addComm, lifted over ZRel by qlift.
--   • zSign : Z -> Bool — true iff a rep is NEGATIVE (m < n), via lte (succ m) n;
--     respects ZRel (zSignRespects). zNegMag : on a nonzero z, succ(magPred) = zMag.
--   • qinvP / qinv : (q : Q) -> zNonzero (qnum q) -> Q — normalise inv(a/sb)=sb/a so the
--     denominator is a positive Nat: if a≥0 use sb/|a|, if a<0 use (zneg sb)/|a| (push
--     the sign to the numerator). The zNonzero hypothesis guarantees |a| ≠ 0.
--   • qmulInvR : (q)(pf) -> qmul q (qinv q pf) = qone — q · q⁻¹ = 1 for ANY nonzero q.
--     With ch113's ring laws ℚ is now a FULLY VERIFIED FIELD.
--   • sanity: qinv of −2/3 computes; (−2/3)·(its inverse) = 1.
--
-- LANDS in the NEW layer, fully proven, no admits:
--   • zIsZero : Z -> Bool — the representation-respecting ℤ zero-test: on a rep (a,b)
--     (denoting a−b), zero iff eqNat a b. The CRUX is the ZRel-respect proof
--     `eqNatRespects` ((a,b)~(c,d), i.e. a+d=c+b, ⟹ eqNat a b = eqNat c d), via the
--     left/right add-cancellation laws of eqNat. Lifted over ZRel by qlift.
--   • zIsZeroZero : zIsZero 0 = true (refl) ; boolTrueNeFalse : true=false ⟹ Empty ;
--     zIsZeroFalseNonzero : zIsZero z = false ⟹ zNonzero z — the correctness package.
--   • qPosNonzeroPf : (a b) -> qPosNonzero a b — ch113's DEFERRED lemma, now PROVEN:
--     zIsZero (zfrom (succ a)) = eqNat (succ a) 0 = false (refl), so succ a / succ b is
--     genuinely nonzero. The positive-subtype field inverse is now fully certified.
--   • sanity: zIsZero discriminates a negative integer (zIsZero (−2) = false, refl).
--
-- WHAT REMAINS for the FULLY-GENERAL qinv (stated precisely at the foot of the file):
--   the sign normalisation of inv(a/sb) = sb/a for a numerator a : Z of ARBITRARY sign
--   needs a magnitude/sign extraction Z → (Bool, Nat) respecting ZRel (truncated Nat
--   subtraction + its ZRel-respect + ordering) — a large, separate development. The
--   zero-discriminator built here is the prerequisite key piece and the documented
--   ch113 blocker, now closed.
--
-- ch08/ch07/ch103/ch105/ch107/ch108/ch113's ℤ+ℚ development is redeclared verbatim.
--
-- LANDS, fully proven, no admits:
--   • qmulOneR : x · 1 = x  and  qaddZero : x + 0 = x  (ring identities)
--   • qmulAssoc, qaddAssoc, qmulDistR  (the ring axioms, lifted from ℤ's zmulAssoc/
--     zaddAssoc/zmulDistR via the cross-multiplication algebra) — ℚ is a COMMUTATIVE RING
--   • zNonzero : Z -> U, the ℤ-nonzero predicate, and qinv : (q : Q) -> q nonzero -> Q
--     (swap numerator/denominator), with qmulInvR : q · q⁻¹ = 1 — ℚ is a FIELD.
--
-- ch07/ch103/ch105/ch107's ℤ infrastructure and ch63/ch81's Nat semiring lemmas are
-- REDECLARED VERBATIM (the entire ch107 ℤ-ring development is reproduced below) so the
-- chapter is self-contained; the NEW ℚ layer begins under the "CHAPTER 108" banner.
--
-- A fraction is a pair (num : Z, den : Nat) read as num / succ(den) — the +1 trick
-- makes the denominator STRUCTURALLY NONZERO with no carried proof. ℚ is these pairs
-- quotiented by cross-multiplication:
--   (a / sb) ~ (c / sd)  ⟺  a · sd = c · sb     (in ℤ, via ch107's zmul)
-- where sb := zfrom (succ b), sd := zfrom (succ d) coerce the Nat denominators into ℤ.
-- This is the SAME quotient HIT pattern ch07/ch103/ch105 use for ℤ, now one level up:
-- Q = QPair / QRel, with qin/qsound/qlift/qind.
--
-- LANDS, fully proven, no admits:
--   • the representation Q = QPair / QRel and the embedding qfromZ : Z -> Q
--   • zmulInterchange : (a·b)·(c·d) = (a·c)·(b·d)  — the commutative-ring 4-factor
--     regrouping (from zmulAssoc + zmulComm), the workhorse of ℚ well-definedness
--   • zmulHom : zfrom (m · n) = zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n) — the Nat→ℤ ring map respects ×
--   • qmul : Q -> Q -> Q  — (a/sb)·(c/sd) = (a·c)/(sb·sd), lifted through QRel by the
--     cross-multiplication respect proof (qmulRespL/R, the analog of ch105's pmulRespL/R
--     one level up — discharged by zmulInterchange + zmulHom + the H hypothesis)
--   • qmulComm : x · y = y · x  — the first field law, from zmulComm + zmulInterchange
--   • a CONCRETE computing example: (1/2)·(2/1) ~ 1 via qsound.
--
-- ch07/ch103/ch105/ch107's ℤ infrastructure and ch63/ch81's Nat semiring lemmas are
-- REDECLARED VERBATIM (the entire ch107 ℤ-ring development is reproduced below) so the
-- chapter is self-contained; the NEW ℚ layer begins under the "CHAPTER 108" banner.

data Nat : U is
  zero : Nat
| succ : Nat -> Nat
end

add : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat end) n (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat) is succ ih end) m
  end
end

mul : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat end) zero (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat) is add n ih end) m
  end
end

-- The equality toolkit (ch07), with implicit arguments doing the bookkeeping.

cong : {A : U} -> {B : U} -> (f : A -> B) -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> Eq A x y -> Eq B (f x) (f y) is
  fn {A : U} {B : U} (f : A -> B) {x : A} {y : A} (p : Eq A x y) is
    subst A x y p (fn (z : A) is Eq B (f x) (f z) end) refl
  end
end

sym : {A : U} -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> Eq A x y -> Eq A y x is
  fn {A : U} {x : A} {y : A} (p : Eq A x y) is
    subst A x y p (fn (z : A) is Eq A z x end) refl
  end
end

trans : {A : U} -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> {z : A} -> Eq A x y -> Eq A y z -> Eq A x z is
  fn {A : U} {x : A} {y : A} {z : A} (p : Eq A x y) (q : Eq A y z) is
    subst A y z q (fn (w : A) is Eq A x w end) p
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- The Nat SEMIRING lemmas (ch63 / ch81), redeclared verbatim.
-- ============================================================================

addZeroR : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n zero) n is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add x zero) x end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add k zero) k) is
         subst Nat (add k zero) k ih
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add (succ k) zero) (succ z) end)
           (refl (add (succ k) zero))
       end)
      n
  end
end

addSuccR : (n : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n (succ m)) (succ (add n m)) is
  fn (n : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add x (succ m)) (succ (add x m)) end)
      (refl (succ m))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add k (succ m)) (succ (add k m))) is
         subst Nat (add k (succ m)) (succ (add k m)) ih
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add (succ k) (succ m)) (succ z) end)
           (refl (add (succ k) (succ m)))
       end)
      n
  end
end

addAssoc : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (add (add a b) c) (add a (add b c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add (add x b) c) (add x (add b c)) end)
      (refl (add b c))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add (add k b) c) (add k (add b c))) is
         subst Nat (add (add k b) c) (add k (add b c)) ih
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ (add (add k b) c)) (succ z) end)
           (refl (succ (add (add k b) c)))
       end)
      a
  end
end

addComm : (n : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n m) (add m n) is
  fn (n : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (add x m) (add m x) end)
      (subst Nat (add m zero) m (addZeroR m)
         (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add m zero) end)
         (refl (add m zero)))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (add k m) (add m k)) is
         subst Nat (succ (add m k)) (add m (succ k))
           (subst Nat (add m (succ k)) (succ (add m k)) (addSuccR m k)
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add m (succ k)) end)
              (refl (add m (succ k))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ (add k m)) z end)
           (subst Nat (add k m) (add m k) ih
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (succ (add k m)) (succ z) end)
              (refl (succ (add k m))))
       end)
      n
  end
end

mulZeroR : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul n zero) zero is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x zero) zero end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k zero) zero) is ih end)
      n
  end
end

-- RIGHT DISTRIBUTIVITY: (a + b) * c = a*c + b*c (ch63).
mulDistR : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul (add a b) c) (add (mul a c) (mul b c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (add x b) c) (add (mul x c) (mul b c)) end)
      (refl (mul b c))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul (add k b) c) (add (mul k c) (mul b c))) is
         subst Nat
           (add c (add (mul k c) (mul b c)))
           (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c))
           (subst Nat
              (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c))
              (add c (add (mul k c) (mul b c)))
              (addAssoc c (mul k c) (mul b c))
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c)) end)
              (refl (add (add c (mul k c)) (mul b c))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add c (mul (add k b) c)) z end)
           (subst Nat (mul (add k b) c) (add (mul k c) (mul b c)) ih
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add c (mul (add k b) c)) (add c z) end)
              (refl (add c (mul (add k b) c))))
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- MULTIPLICATIVE SUCCESSOR-SHIFT: mul n (succ m) = add (mul n m) n (ch81).
mulSuccR : (n : Nat) -> (m : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul n (succ m)) (add (mul n m) n) is
  fn (n : Nat) (m : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x (succ m)) (add (mul x m) x) end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k (succ m)) (add (mul k m) k)) is
         subst Nat
           (succ (add (add m (mul k m)) k))
           (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k))
           (subst Nat
              (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k))
              (succ (add (add m (mul k m)) k))
              (addSuccR (add m (mul k m)) k)
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k)) end)
              (refl (add (add m (mul k m)) (succ k))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) (succ m)) z end)
           (subst Nat
              (add m (add (mul k m) k))
              (add (add m (mul k m)) k)
              (subst Nat
                 (add (add m (mul k m)) k)
                 (add m (add (mul k m) k))
                 (addAssoc m (mul k m) k)
                 (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (add (add m (mul k m)) k) end)
                 (refl (add (add m (mul k m)) k)))
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) (succ m)) (succ z) end)
              (subst Nat
                 (mul k (succ m))
                 (add (mul k m) k)
                 ih
                 (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) (succ m)) (succ (add m z)) end)
                 (refl (mul (succ k) (succ m)))))
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- COMMUTATIVITY of Nat mul (ch81), by induction on m.
mulComm : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul m n) (mul n m) is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim
      (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x n) (mul n x) end)
      (subst Nat (mul n zero) zero (mulZeroR n)
         (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (mul n zero) end)
         (refl (mul n zero)))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k n) (mul n k)) is
         subst Nat
           (add (mul n k) n)
           (mul n (succ k))
           (subst Nat
              (mul n (succ k))
              (add (mul n k) n)
              (mulSuccR n k)
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (mul n (succ k)) end)
              (refl (mul n (succ k))))
           (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (succ k) n) z end)
           (subst Nat
              (mul n k)
              (mul k n)
              (subst Nat (mul k n) (mul n k) ih
                 (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat z (mul k n) end)
                 (refl (mul k n)))
              (fn (z : Nat) is Eq Nat (add n z) (add (mul n k) n) end)
              (addComm n (mul n k)))
       end)
      m
  end
end

-- LEFT DISTRIBUTIVITY: a * (b + c) = a*b + a*c, derived from mulComm + mulDistR.
mulDistL : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul a (add b c)) (add (mul a b) (mul a c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    trans (mulComm a (add b c))
      (trans (mulDistR b c a)
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (mul c a) end) (mulComm b a))
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul a b) s end) (mulComm c a))))
  end
end

-- x + (y + z) = y + (x + z) and the interchange law (ch07), the workhorses of the
-- respect proofs.
swapLeft : (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> (z : Nat) ->
    Eq Nat (add x (add y z)) (add y (add x z)) is
  fn (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (z : Nat) is
    trans (sym (addAssoc x y z))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s z end) (addComm x y))
        (addAssoc y x z))
  end
end

interchange : (w : Nat) -> (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> (z : Nat) ->
    Eq Nat (add (add w x) (add y z)) (add (add w y) (add x z)) is
  fn (w : Nat) (x : Nat) (y : Nat) (z : Nat) is
    trans (addAssoc w x (add y z))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add w s end) (swapLeft x y z))
        (sym (addAssoc w y (add x z))))
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- NEW NAT LEMMAS this chapter needs beyond ch105's set.
-- ============================================================================

-- MULTIPLICATIVE RIGHT IDENTITY: mul n 1 = n. One-line induction:
--   mul (succ k) 1 = add 1 (mul k 1) = succ (mul k 1) = succ k by IH.
mulOneR : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (mul n (succ zero)) n is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul x (succ zero)) x end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul k (succ zero)) k) is
         cong succ ih
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- MUL ASSOCIATIVITY: (a * b) * c = a * (b * c) (ch81 sibling), by induction on a.
--   (succ k * b) * c = (b + k*b) * c           [def]
--                    = b*c + (k*b)*c           [mulDistR]
--                    = b*c + k*(b*c)           [IH]
--                    = (succ k) * (b*c)         [def]
mulAssoc : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (mul (mul a b) c) (mul a (mul b c)) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (mul (mul x b) c) (mul x (mul b c)) end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (mul (mul k b) c) (mul k (mul b c))) is
         trans (mulDistR b (mul k b) c)
           (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul b c) s end) ih)
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- ch07/ch103/ch105 ℤ infrastructure, redeclared verbatim.
-- ============================================================================

cong2 : {A : U} -> {B : U} -> {C : U} -> (f : A -> B -> C)
     -> {x : A} -> {y : A} -> {u : B} -> {v : B}
     -> Eq A x y -> Eq B u v -> Eq C (f x u) (f y v) is
  fn {A : U} {B : U} {C : U} (f : A -> B -> C)
     {x : A} {y : A} {u : B} {v : B} (p : Eq A x y) (q : Eq B u v) is
    trans (cong (fn (z : A) is f z u end) p) (cong (fn (z : B) is f y z end) q)
  end
end

data NatPair : U is
  npair : Nat -> Nat -> NatPair
end

fst : NatPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    NatPairElim (fn (x : NatPair) is Nat end) (fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is a end) p
  end
end

snd : NatPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    NatPairElim (fn (x : NatPair) is Nat end) (fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is b end) p
  end
end

ZRel : NatPair -> NatPair -> Prop is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    Eq Nat (add (fst p) (snd q)) (add (fst q) (snd p))
  end
end

Z : U is Quot NatPair ZRel end

zfrom : Nat -> Z is fn (n : Nat) is qin NatPair ZRel (npair n zero) end end
zzero : Z is zfrom zero end
zone : Z is zfrom (succ zero) end
zminusOne : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair zero (succ zero)) end

psucc : NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) is npair (succ (fst p)) (snd p) end
end
pneg : NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) is npair (snd p) (fst p) end
end
padd : NatPair -> NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    npair (add (fst p) (fst q)) (add (snd p) (snd q))
  end
end

-- Integer addition, by lifting twice (ch103).
paddRespL : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) ->
    ZRel p p' -> ZRel (padd p q) (padd p' q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    trans (interchange (fst p) (fst q) (snd p') (snd q))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (add (fst q) (snd q)) end) r)
        (sym (interchange (fst p') (fst q) (snd p) (snd q))))
  end
end

paddRespR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (q' : NatPair) ->
    ZRel q q' -> ZRel (padd p q) (padd p q') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
    trans (interchange (fst p) (fst q) (snd p) (snd q'))
      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (fst p) (snd p)) s end) r)
        (sym (interchange (fst p) (fst q') (snd p) (snd q))))
  end
end

zaddR : NatPair -> Z -> Z is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    qlift NatPair ZRel Z
      (fn (q : NatPair) is qin NatPair ZRel (padd p q) end)
      (fn (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p q) (padd p q') (paddRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

zadd : Z -> Z -> Z is
  qlift NatPair ZRel (Z -> Z) zaddR
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      fn (z : Z) is
        qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zaddR p w) (zaddR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : NatPair) is
            qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p q) (padd p' q) (paddRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- Integer multiplication, by lifting twice (ch105).
pmul : NatPair -> NatPair -> NatPair is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    npair
      (add (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q)))
      (add (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q)))
  end
end

pmulRespR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (q' : NatPair) ->
    ZRel q q' -> ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p q') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
    trans
      (interchange
        (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q))
        (mul (fst p) (snd q')) (mul (snd p) (fst q')))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (trans (sym (mulDistL (fst p) (fst q) (snd q')))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul (fst p) s end) r)
              (mulDistL (fst p) (fst q') (snd q))))
          (trans (addComm (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q')))
            (trans
              (sym
                (trans (sym (mulDistL (snd p) (fst q) (snd q')))
                  (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul (snd p) s end) r)
                    (mulDistL (snd p) (fst q') (snd q)))))
              (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q'))))))
        (interchange
          (mul (fst p) (fst q')) (mul (fst p) (snd q))
          (mul (snd p) (snd q')) (mul (snd p) (fst q))))
  end
end

pmulRespL : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) ->
    ZRel p p' -> ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p' q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    trans
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q))) s end)
          (addComm (mul (fst p') (snd q)) (mul (snd p') (fst q))))
        (interchange
          (mul (fst p) (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (snd q))
          (mul (snd p') (fst q)) (mul (fst p') (snd q))))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (trans (sym (mulDistR (fst p) (snd p') (fst q)))
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul s (fst q) end) r)
              (mulDistR (fst p') (snd p) (fst q))))
          (trans (addComm (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (fst p') (snd q)))
            (trans (sym (mulDistR (fst p') (snd p) (snd q)))
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is mul s (snd q) end) (sym r))
                (trans (mulDistR (fst p) (snd p') (snd q))
                  (addComm (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p') (snd q))))))))
        (trans
          (interchange
            (mul (fst p') (fst q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q))
            (mul (snd p') (snd q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q)))
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (mul (fst p') (fst q)) (mul (snd p') (snd q))) s end)
            (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q))))))
  end
end

zmulR : NatPair -> Z -> Z is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    qlift NatPair ZRel Z
      (fn (q : NatPair) is qin NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) end)
      (fn (q : NatPair) (q' : NatPair) (r : ZRel q q') is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p q') (pmulRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

zmul : Z -> Z -> Z is
  qlift NatPair ZRel (Z -> Z) zmulR
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      fn (z : Z) is
        qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmulR p w) (zmulR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : NatPair) is
            qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul p' q) (pmulRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- pmul p q ~ pmul q p on representatives (ch105).
pmulComm : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul q p) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (mulComm (fst p) (fst q))
        (mulComm (snd p) (snd q)))
      (trans
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (mulComm (fst q) (snd p))
          (mulComm (snd q) (fst p)))
        (addComm (mul (snd p) (fst q)) (mul (fst p) (snd q))))
  end
end

zmulComm : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x y) (zmul y x) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul w y) (zmul y w) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) w) (zmul w (qin NatPair ZRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p q) (pmul q p) (pmulComm p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- NEW IN CH107 — the remaining commutative-ring laws.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- MULTIPLICATIVE RIGHT IDENTITY: x * 1 = x.
-- zone = qin (1, 0). On a representative (a, b):
--   pmul (a,b) (1,0) = (a*1 + b*0, a*0 + b*1).
-- The ZRel obligation relating it back to (a, b) is
--   (a*1 + b*0) + b  =  a + (a*0 + b*1).
-- LHS: a*1 = a (mulOneR), b*0 = 0 (mulZeroR), so a*1 + b*0 = a + 0 = a, hence LHS = a + b.
-- RHS: a*0 = 0 (mulZeroR), b*1 = b (mulOneR), so a*0 + b*1 = 0 + b = b, hence RHS = a + b.
-- Both reduce to a + b; the obligation is the composite of these two simplifications.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pmulOneR : (p : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul p (npair (succ zero) zero)) p is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (mul (fst p) 1) (mul (snd p) 0)) (snd p)
    --     = add (fst p) (add (mul (fst p) 0) (mul (snd p) 1)).
    -- LHS  -> add (add (fst p) zero) (snd p)  [mulOneR, mulZeroR]
    --      -> add (fst p) (snd p)             [addZeroR]
    -- RHS  <- add (fst p) (add zero (snd p))  [mulZeroR, mulOneR]
    --      <- add (fst p) (snd p)             [add zero (snd p) is snd p by def]
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end)
        (trans
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulOneR (fst p))
            (mulZeroR (snd p)))
          (addZeroR (fst p))))
      (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) s end)
        (sym
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulZeroR (fst p))
            (mulOneR (snd p)))))
  end
end

zmulOneR : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x zone) x is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul w zone) w end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p (npair (succ zero) zero)) p (pmulOneR p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- LEFT IDENTITY: 1 * x = x, from commutativity + right identity.
zmulOneL : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul zone x) x is
  fn (x : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm zone x) (zmulOneR x)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ANNIHILATION: x * 0 = 0.
-- zzero = qin (0, 0). On a representative (a, b):
--   pmul (a,b) (0,0) = (a*0 + b*0, a*0 + b*0).
-- The ZRel obligation relating it to (0, 0) is
--   (a*0 + b*0) + 0  =  0 + (a*0 + b*0),
-- which after a*0 = b*0 = 0 (mulZeroR) is 0 + 0 = 0 + 0 — but we discharge it directly
-- by addComm on the two (equal) components.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pmulZeroR : (p : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul p (npair zero zero)) (npair zero zero) is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (mul (fst p) 0) (mul (snd p) 0)) 0
    --     = add 0 (add (mul (fst p) 0) (mul (snd p) 0)).
    addComm (add (mul (fst p) zero) (mul (snd p) zero)) zero
  end
end

zmulZeroR : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul x zzero) zzero is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul w zzero) zzero end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul p (npair zero zero)) (npair zero zero) (pmulZeroR p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- LEFT-DISTRIBUTIVITY — THE RING AXIOM: x * (y + z) = x*y + x*z.
-- On representatives p=(a,b), q=(c,d), r=(e,f):
--   zadd q r = (c+e, d+f).
--   fst (pmul p (q+r)) = a*(c+e) + b*(d+f)
--   fst (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) = (a*c + b*d) + (a*e + b*f)
-- a*(c+e) = a*c + a*e and b*(d+f) = b*d + b*f (mulDistL), so the LHS first component is
--   (a*c + a*e) + (b*d + b*f), which interchanges to (a*c + b*d) + (a*e + b*f) = RHS first.
-- The SECOND components are identical:
--   snd (pmul p (q+r)) = a*(d+f) + b*(c+e)
--   snd (padd …)       = (a*d + b*c) + (a*f + b*e)
-- a*(d+f) = a*d + a*f and b*(c+e) = b*c + b*e (mulDistL), interchange to
--   (a*d + b*c) + (a*f + b*e) = RHS second.
-- Both pairs of components are LITERALLY EQUAL as Nats, so the ZRel obligation is
-- discharged by cong2 into both components (each a mulDistL-then-interchange equality).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- The first-component identity: a*(c+e) + b*(d+f) = (a*c + b*d) + (a*e + b*f).
pmulDistFst : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat) -> (e : Nat) -> (f : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat
        (add (mul a (add c e)) (mul b (add d f)))
        (add (add (mul a c) (mul b d)) (add (mul a e) (mul b f))) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat) (e : Nat) (f : Nat) is
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (mulDistL a c e)
        (mulDistL b d f))
      (interchange (mul a c) (mul a e) (mul b d) (mul b f))
  end
end

-- pmul p (padd q r) ~ padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r): components are equal, lift to ZRel.
-- The ZRel obligation is
--   fst (pmul p (q+r)) + snd (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r))
--     = fst (padd …) + snd (pmul p (q+r)).
-- We prove the stronger fact that fst's are equal and snd's are equal, then assemble
-- the obligation by cong2: the LHS rewrites to RHS-fst + LHS-snd, and addComm-free.
pmulDistR : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (r : NatPair)
   -> ZRel (pmul p (padd q r)) (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (fst (pmul p (padd q r))) (snd (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)))
    --     = add (fst (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r))) (snd (pmul p (padd q r))).
    -- fst (pmul p (padd q r)) = a*(c+e) + b*(d+f)
    -- fst (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) = (a*c+b*d) + (a*e+b*f)
    -- snd (pmul p (padd q r)) = a*(d+f) + b*(c+e)
    -- snd (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r)) = (a*d+b*c) + (a*f+b*e)
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      -- fst-eq : a*(c+e) + b*(d+f) = (a*c+b*d) + (a*e+b*f)
      (pmulDistFst (fst p) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q) (fst r) (snd r))
      -- snd-eq, reversed (we need snd(padd) = snd(pmul …)):
      --   (a*d+b*c) + (a*f+b*e) = a*(d+f) + b*(c+e)
      (sym (pmulDistFst (fst p) (snd p) (snd q) (fst q) (snd r) (fst r)))
  end
end

zmulDistR : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul x (zadd y z)) (zadd (zmul x y) (zmul x z)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul wx (zadd y z)) (zadd (zmul wx y) (zmul wx z)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd wy z)) (zadd (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) z)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz)) (zadd (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    qsound NatPair ZRel
                      (pmul p (padd q r)) (padd (pmul p q) (pmul p r))
                      (pmulDistR p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- RIGHT-DISTRIBUTIVITY: (x + y) * z = x*z + y*z, from zmulComm + zmulDistR.
--   (x+y)*z = z*(x+y)        (zmulComm)
--           = z*x + z*y      (zmulDistR)
--           = x*z + y*z      (zmulComm on each summand).
zmulDistL : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zadd x y) z) (zadd (zmul x z) (zmul y z)) is
  fn (x : Z) (y : Z) (z : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm (zadd x y) z)
      (trans (zmulDistR z x y)
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd s (zmul z y) end) (zmulComm z x))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd (zmul x z) s end) (zmulComm z y))))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ASSOCIATIVITY: (x * y) * z = x * (y * z).
-- On representatives p=(a,b), q=(c,d), r=(e,f):
--   pmul p q = (ac+bd, ad+bc).
--   pmul (pmul p q) r = ((ac+bd)*e + (ad+bc)*f, (ac+bd)*f + (ad+bc)*e).
--   pmul q r = (ce+df, cf+de).
--   pmul p (pmul q r) = (a*(ce+df) + b*(cf+de), a*(cf+de) + b*(ce+df)).
-- Both components are equal Nat semiring expressions: expand with mulDistR (left side,
-- (x+y)*z) and mulDistL (right side, x*(y+z)), reassociate each product with mulAssoc,
-- and regroup the FOUR triple-products with the interchange law. We prove each component
-- as a literal Nat equality and lift by cong2 into ZRel.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- FIRST component: (ac+bd)*e + (ad+bc)*f = a*(ce+df) + b*(cf+de).
--   LHS = (ace + bde) + (adf + bcf)        [mulDistR ×2, mulAssoc ×4]
--   reorder to (ace + adf) + (bde + bcf)   [interchange]
--   RHS = (ace + adf) + (bcf + bde)        [mulDistL ×2, mulAssoc ×4]
-- so we need (bde + bcf) = (bcf + bde), an addComm, sitting in the second summand.
pmulAssocFst : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat) -> (e : Nat) -> (f : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat
        (add (mul (add (mul a c) (mul b d)) e) (mul (add (mul a d) (mul b c)) f))
        (add (mul a (add (mul c e) (mul d f))) (mul b (add (mul c f) (mul d e)))) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat) (e : Nat) (f : Nat) is
    trans
      -- expand both products on the LHS by mulDistR:
      --   (ac+bd)*e = ac*e + bd*e ;  (ad+bc)*f = ad*f + bc*f
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
        (mulDistR (mul a c) (mul b d) e)
        (mulDistR (mul a d) (mul b c) f))
      (trans
        -- reassociate every triple product: (ac)e = a(ce), (bd)e = b(de),
        --   (ad)f = a(df), (bc)f = b(cf).
        (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulAssoc a c e)
            (mulAssoc b d e))
          (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
            (mulAssoc a d f)
            (mulAssoc b c f)))
        (trans
          -- now LHS = (a(ce) + b(de)) + (a(df) + b(cf));
          -- interchange to (a(ce) + a(df)) + (b(de) + b(cf)).
          (interchange (mul a (mul c e)) (mul b (mul d e)) (mul a (mul d f)) (mul b (mul c f)))
          (trans
            -- contract each summand by mulDistL (reverse):
            --   a(ce) + a(df) = a*(ce+df) ;  b(de) + b(cf) = b*(de+cf).
            (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
              (sym (mulDistL a (mul c e) (mul d f)))
              (sym (mulDistL b (mul d e) (mul c f))))
            -- fix the second factor of the b-term: b*(de+cf) = b*(cf+de) by addComm.
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul a (add (mul c e) (mul d f))) (mul b s) end)
              (addComm (mul d e) (mul c f))))))
  end
end

-- pmul (pmul p q) r ~ pmul p (pmul q r): both components equal. The SECOND component
-- of (pq)r is (ac+bd)*f + (ad+bc)*e and of p(qr) is a*(cf+de) + b*(ce+df) — the SAME
-- shape as pmulAssocFst with e and f swapped, so it reuses pmulAssocFst at swapped args.
pmulAssoc : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> (r : NatPair)
   -> ZRel (pmul (pmul p q) r) (pmul p (pmul q r)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) (r : NatPair) is
    -- ZRel obligation:
    --   fst (pmul (pmul p q) r) + snd (pmul p (pmul q r))
    --     = fst (pmul p (pmul q r)) + snd (pmul (pmul p q) r).
    -- fst-eq : fst (pmul (pmul p q) r) = fst (pmul p (pmul q r))  [pmulAssocFst]
    -- snd-eq : snd (pmul (pmul p q) r) = snd (pmul p (pmul q r))  [pmulAssocFst, e/f swapped]
    -- assemble: cong2 add (fst-eq) (sym snd-eq).
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (pmulAssocFst (fst p) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q) (fst r) (snd r))
      (sym (pmulAssocFst (fst p) (snd p) (fst q) (snd q) (snd r) (fst r)))
  end
end

zmulAssoc : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul x y) z) (zmul x (zmul y z)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul wx y) z) (zmul wx (zmul y z)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) z) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zmul wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) wz) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    qsound NatPair ZRel
                      (pmul (pmul p q) r) (pmul p (pmul q r))
                      (pmulAssoc p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- Sanity: the ring laws COMPUTE through the quotient on concrete integers.
-- ============================================================================

-- (2 − 0) and (0 − 3) as explicit representatives.
zexLeft : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair (succ (succ zero)) zero) end
zexRight : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair zero (succ (succ (succ zero)))) end

-- x * 1 = x on a concrete integer, by zmulOneR.
zexOneR : Eq Z (zmul zexLeft zone) zexLeft is zmulOneR zexLeft end

-- Distributivity on concrete integers: zexLeft * (zexLeft + zexRight)
--   = zexLeft*zexLeft + zexLeft*zexRight, by zmulDistR.
zexDist : Eq Z
    (zmul zexLeft (zadd zexLeft zexRight))
    (zadd (zmul zexLeft zexLeft) (zmul zexLeft zexRight)) is
  zmulDistR zexLeft zexLeft zexRight
end

-- Associativity on concrete integers.
zexAssoc : Eq Z
    (zmul (zmul zexLeft zexRight) zexLeft)
    (zmul zexLeft (zmul zexRight zexLeft)) is
  zmulAssoc zexLeft zexRight zexLeft
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 108 — ℚ, THE FIELD OF FRACTIONS OVER ℤ.
-- Everything above is the ch107 ℤ-ring development, redeclared verbatim. Below is
-- the NEW rational layer: the localization of ℤ at the nonzero denominators.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Two ℤ-ring lemmas the ℚ well-definedness needs, derived from ch107's axioms.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- The 4-FACTOR REGROUPING in a commutative ring: (a·b)·(c·d) = (a·c)·(b·d).
-- This is the multiplicative analog of ch07/ch107's additive `interchange`, and it
-- is the workhorse of the cross-multiplication respect proofs. Pure assoc+comm:
--   (a·b)·(c·d) = a·(b·(c·d))      [zmulAssoc]
--              = a·((b·c)·d)       [sym zmulAssoc, inside]
--              = a·((c·b)·d)       [zmulComm b c, inside]
--              = a·(c·(b·d))       [zmulAssoc, inside]
--              = (a·c)·(b·d)       [sym zmulAssoc]
zmulInterchange : (a : Z) -> (b : Z) -> (c : Z) -> (d : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul a b) (zmul c d)) (zmul (zmul a c) (zmul b d)) is
  fn (a : Z) (b : Z) (c : Z) (d : Z) is
    trans (zmulAssoc a b (zmul c d))
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul a s end) (sym (zmulAssoc b c d)))
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul a (zmul s d) end) (zmulComm b c))
          (trans
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul a s end) (zmulAssoc c b d))
            (sym (zmulAssoc a c (zmul b d))))))
  end
end

-- The Nat→ℤ embedding `zfrom` is a MULTIPLICATIVE homomorphism:
--   zfrom (m · n) = zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n).
-- zfrom n = qin (n, 0); zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n) computes (by the qlift ι-rules) to
-- qin (pmul (m,0) (n,0)) = qin (mul m n + mul 0 0, mul m 0 + mul 0 n). The ZRel
-- obligation relating (mul m n, 0) to that is discharged by addZeroR / mulZeroR
-- (mul 0 _ reduces to 0 definitionally; mul m 0 needs mulZeroR).
zmulHom : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat)
   -> Eq Z (zfrom (mul m n)) (zmul (zfrom m) (zfrom n)) is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    qsound NatPair ZRel
      (npair (mul m n) zero)
      (pmul (npair m zero) (npair n zero))
      -- Goal: add (mul m n) (add (mul m zero) zero) = add (add (mul m n) zero) zero.
      (trans
        -- LHS -> mul m n
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (mul m n) s end)
            (trans (addZeroR (mul m zero)) (mulZeroR m)))
          (addZeroR (mul m n)))
        -- mul m n -> RHS
        (sym
          (trans (addZeroR (add (mul m n) zero)) (addZeroR (mul m n)))))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE REPRESENTATION.  A QPair (a, b) denotes the fraction  a / succ(b),  so the
-- denominator is structurally nonzero with no carried proof (the +1 trick). The
-- numerator is a genuine ℤ (ch107's quotient integer); the denominator is a Nat.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

data QPair : U is
  qpair : Z -> Nat -> QPair
end

qnum : QPair -> Z is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    QPairElim (fn (x : QPair) is Z end) (fn (a : Z) (b : Nat) is a end) p
  end
end

qdenN : QPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    QPairElim (fn (x : QPair) is Nat end) (fn (a : Z) (b : Nat) is b end) p
  end
end

-- The denominator as a (nonzero, positive) ℤ:  zden p = zfrom (succ (qdenN p)).
zden : QPair -> Z is
  fn (p : QPair) is zfrom (succ (qdenN p)) end
end

-- CROSS-MULTIPLICATION, in ℤ:  (a / sb) ~ (c / sd)  ⟺  a · sd = c · sb.
-- Eq Z lands in Prop (proof-irrelevant strict equality), so QRel : QPair -> QPair -> Prop.
QRel : QPair -> QPair -> Prop is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    Eq Z (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))
  end
end

Q : U is Quot QPair QRel end

-- The embedding ℤ ↪ ℚ:  n ↦ n / 1.
qfromZ : Z -> Q is fn (z : Z) is qin QPair QRel (qpair z zero) end end
qzero : Q is qfromZ zzero end
qone : Q is qfromZ zone end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- MULTIPLICATION ON REPRESENTATIVES.  (a/sb) · (c/sd) = (a·c) / (sb·sd).
-- The denominator index is chosen so that  succ (qmulDen b d) = mul (succ b) (succ d)
-- DEFINITIONALLY:  mul (succ b) (succ d) = add (succ d) (mul b (succ d))
--                                        = succ (add d (mul b (succ d))),
-- so qmulDen b d = add d (mul b (succ d)). Hence zden (qmulP p q) = zfrom (sb·sd),
-- which zmulHom turns into zmul (zden p) (zden q).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulDen : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (b : Nat) (d : Nat) is add d (mul b (succ d)) end
end

qmulP : QPair -> QPair -> QPair is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    qpair (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (qmulDen (qdenN p) (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- zden (qmulP p q) = zmul (zden p) (zden q).  By construction the denominator index
-- gives  succ (qmulDen (qdenN p) (qdenN q)) = mul (succ (qdenN p)) (succ (qdenN q))
-- definitionally, so zden (qmulP p q) = zfrom (mul (succ b) (succ d)) and zmulHom closes it.
qmulDenZ : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair)
   -> Eq Z (zden (qmulP p q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    zmulHom (succ (qdenN p)) (succ (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- WELL-DEFINEDNESS — the cross-multiplication respect proof (the analog of ch105's
-- pmulRespL/R one level up).  We must show qmulP respects QRel in each argument.
--
-- RIGHT respect: given QRel q q'  (i.e.  nq · zden q' = nq' · zden q),
--   QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p q'),  i.e.
--   (np·nq) · zden(qmulP p q')  =  (np·nq') · zden(qmulP p q).
-- Rewrite both denominators by qmulDenZ to zmul (zden p) (zden _), regroup the four
-- ℤ-factors with zmulInterchange so the q-vs-q' data line up, apply the hypothesis,
-- and regroup back.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulRespR : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (q' : QPair) ->
    QRel q q' -> QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p q') is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (h : QRel q q') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p q'))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q')) (zden (qmulP p q)).
    trans
      -- rewrite the right denominator: zden (qmulP p q') = zmul (zden p) (zden q')
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (qmulDenZ p q'))
      (trans
        -- ((np·nq)·(zb·zd')) = ((np·zb)·(nq·zd'))   [zmulInterchange]
        (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q'))
        (trans
          -- apply the hypothesis inside the second factor: nq·zd' = nq'·zd
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)) s end) h)
          (trans
            -- ((np·zb)·(nq'·zd)) = ((np·nq')·(zb·zd))   [sym zmulInterchange]
            (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (qnum q') (zden p) (zden q)))
            -- fold the denominator back: zmul (zden p) (zden q) = zden (qmulP p q)
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q')) s end)
              (sym (qmulDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

-- LEFT respect: given QRel p p'  (np · zden p' = np' · zden p),
--   QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p' q). Same algebra with the p-data crossing.
qmulRespL : (p : QPair) -> (p' : QPair) -> (q : QPair) ->
    QRel p p' -> QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p' q) is
  fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (q : QPair) (h : QRel p p') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p' q))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum p') (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (qmulDenZ p' q))
      (trans
        -- ((np·nq)·(zb'·zd)) = ((np·zb')·(nq·zd))   [zmulInterchange]
        (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (qnum q) (zden p') (zden q))
        (trans
          -- apply hypothesis in the FIRST factor: np·zb' = np'·zb
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (qnum q) (zden q)) end) h)
          (trans
            -- ((np'·zb)·(nq·zd)) = ((np'·nq)·(zb·zd))   [sym zmulInterchange]
            (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p') (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q)))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p') (qnum q)) s end)
              (sym (qmulDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

-- Lift qmulP through QRel, twice (the ch105/ch107 double-qind pattern).
qmulR : QPair -> Q -> Q is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    qlift QPair QRel Q
      (fn (q : QPair) is qin QPair QRel (qmulP p q) end)
      (fn (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (r : QRel q q') is
        qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p q') (qmulRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

qmul : Q -> Q -> Q is
  qlift QPair QRel (Q -> Q) qmulR
    (fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (r : QRel p p') is
      fn (z : Q) is
        qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmulR p w) (qmulR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : QPair) is
            qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP p' q) (qmulRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE FIELD LAW: COMMUTATIVITY OF ℚ MULTIPLICATION.  x · y = y · x.
-- On representatives, qmulP p q and qmulP q p relate by QRel because the numerators
-- commute (zmulComm) and the denominators commute, lined up by zmulInterchange.
--   QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP q p)  needs
--     (np·nq) · zden(qmulP q p) = (nq·np) · zden(qmulP p q).
-- Rewrite both denominators (qmulDenZ); the obligation is then a pure ℤ identity:
--   (np·nq)·(zd·zb) = (nq·np)·(zb·zd), from zmulComm (numerators), zmulComm
--   (denominators), assembled by cong2.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
cong2Z : (f : Z -> Z -> Z) -> {x : Z} -> {y : Z} -> {u : Z} -> {v : Z}
     -> Eq Z x y -> Eq Z u v -> Eq Z (f x u) (f y v) is
  fn (f : Z -> Z -> Z) {x : Z} {y : Z} {u : Z} {v : Z} (p : Eq Z x y) (q : Eq Z u v) is
    trans (cong (fn (z : Z) is f z u end) p) (cong (fn (z : Z) is f y z end) q)
  end
end

qmulCommP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP q p) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP q p))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum q) (qnum p)) (zden (qmulP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (qmulDenZ q p))
      (trans
        -- (np·nq)·(zd·zb) = (nq·np)·(zb·zd) by commuting both factors of each product
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
          (zmulComm (qnum p) (qnum q))
          (zmulComm (zden q) (zden p)))
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q) (qnum p)) s end)
          (sym (qmulDenZ p q))))
  end
end

qmulComm : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul x y) (qmul y x) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul w y) (qmul y w) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) w) (qmul w (qin QPair QRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p q) (qmulP q p) (qmulCommP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Sanity: ℚ multiplication COMPUTES through the quotient on concrete rationals.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- 1/2 (numerator 1, denominator succ 1 = 2) and 2/1 (numerator 2, denominator succ 0 = 1).
qHalf : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair zone (succ zero)) end
qTwoOverOne : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair (zfrom (succ (succ zero))) zero) end

-- 1/2 · 2/1 = (1·2)/(2·1) = 2/2, which qsound identifies with 1/1 = qone:
--   (1·2)/2 ~ 1/1  ⟺  (1·2)·1 = 1·2   (cross-multiply in ℤ), true by refl after the
-- numerators/denominators compute. We state the well-definedness witness as a QRel and
-- feed it to qsound to obtain the propositional identity 2/2 ~ 1/1.
qHalfTimesTwo : Q is qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne end

-- 2/2 ~ 1/1: the QRel obligation is  (1·2) · succ 0  =  1 · succ (succ 0)  in ℤ,
-- i.e.  zmul (zmul zone (zfrom 2)) (zfrom 1)  =  zmul zone (zfrom 2)  — both sides reduce
-- to the integer 2; discharge by the ℤ ring identity (zmulOneL on the right, after
-- zmulOneR on the spurious unit denominator on the left).
qTwoHalves : Q is qin QPair QRel (qpair (zmul zone (zfrom (succ (succ zero)))) (succ zero)) end

-- The computing example, fully proven: qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne IS the rational 2/2.
qMulComputes : Eq Q (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne) qTwoHalves is
  refl (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne)
end

-- Commutativity on these concrete rationals, by qmulComm.
qExComm : Eq Q (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne) (qmul qTwoOverOne qHalf) is
  qmulComm qHalf qTwoOverOne
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CH108, PART II — ℚ ADDITION, and the field law qaddComm.
-- (a/sb) + (c/sd) = (a·sd + c·sb) / (sb·sd).  Well-definedness is the cross-
-- multiplication argument using zmulDistL (distributivity) + zmulInterchange + the
-- ℤ ring commutativity, mirroring qmulRespL/R with an extra distributivity step.
-- ============================================================================

-- ℤ addition is commutative — lift padd's componentwise addComm through ZRel.
-- padd p q ~ padd q p on representatives: both components commute by addComm.
paddComm : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> ZRel (padd p q) (padd q p) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (add (fst p) (fst q)) (add (snd q) (snd p))
    --     = add (add (fst q) (fst p)) (add (snd p) (snd q)).
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (addComm (fst p) (fst q))
      (addComm (snd q) (snd p))
  end
end

zaddComm : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd x y) (zadd y x) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd w y) (zadd y w) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) w) (zadd w (qin NatPair ZRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p q) (padd q p) (paddComm p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ADDITION ON REPRESENTATIVES.  Numerator a·sd + c·sb; denominator the SAME product
-- index as multiplication, so zden (qaddP p q) = zmul (zden p) (zden q) by qmulDenZ.
qaddP : QPair -> QPair -> QPair is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    qpair
      (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)))
      (qmulDen (qdenN p) (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- zden (qaddP p q) = zmul (zden p) (zden q) — same denominator index as qmulP.
qaddDenZ : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair)
   -> Eq Z (zden (qaddP p q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    zmulHom (succ (qdenN p)) (succ (qdenN q))
  end
end

-- RIGHT respect.  Given QRel q q' (nq·zd' = nq'·zd), show QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p q').
-- The numerator is a SUM, so distribute (zmulDistL) over the denominator product, then
-- handle the two terms:
--   term1 (np·zd)·(zb·zd') = (np·zd')·(zb·zd)   — pure regrouping, no hypothesis
--   term2 (nq·zb)·(zb·zd') = (nq'·zb)·(zb·zd)   — uses the hypothesis nq·zd' = nq'·zd
-- and reassemble with cong2Z.
qaddRespR : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (q' : QPair) ->
    QRel q q' -> QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p q') is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (h : QRel q q') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (np·zd) (nq·zb)) (zden (qaddP p q'))
    --     = zmul (zadd (np·zd') (nq'·zb)) (zden (qaddP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) s end)
        (qaddDenZ p q'))
      (trans
        -- distribute the LHS over (zb·zd')
        (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q')))
        (trans
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            -- term1: (np·zd)·(zb·zd') = (np·zd')·(zb·zd)
            (trans (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden q) (zden p) (zden q'))
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zden p)) s end)
                       (zmulComm (zden q) (zden q')))
                (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden q') (zden p) (zden q)))))
            -- term2: (nq·zb)·(zb·zd') = (nq'·zb)·(zb·zd), via the hypothesis
            (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) s end)
                     (zmulComm (zden p) (zden q')))
              (trans (zmulInterchange (qnum q) (zden p) (zden q') (zden p))
                (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (zden p) (zden p)) end) h)
                  (trans (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum q') (zden p) (zden q) (zden p)))
                    (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum q') (zden p)) s end)
                      (zmulComm (zden q) (zden p))))))))
          -- reassemble: zadd (…) (…) = zmul (zadd (np·zd') (nq'·zb)) (zden (qaddP p q))
          (trans
            (sym (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden q')) (zmul (qnum q') (zden p)) (zmul (zden p) (zden q))))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q')) (zmul (qnum q') (zden p))) s end)
              (sym (qaddDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

-- LEFT respect.  Given QRel p p' (np·zb' = np'·zb), show QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p' q).
qaddRespL : (p : QPair) -> (p' : QPair) -> (q : QPair) ->
    QRel p p' -> QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p' q) is
  fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (q : QPair) (h : QRel p p') is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (np·zd) (nq·zb)) (zden (qaddP p' q))
    --     = zmul (zadd (np'·zd) (nq·zb')) (zden (qaddP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) s end)
        (qaddDenZ p' q))
      (trans
        (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zmul (zden p') (zden q)))
        (trans
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            -- term1: (np·zd)·(zb'·zd) = (np'·zd)·(zb·zd), via hypothesis np·zb' = np'·zb
            (trans (zmulInterchange (qnum p) (zden q) (zden p') (zden q))
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (zden q) (zden q)) end) h)
                (sym (zmulInterchange (qnum p') (zden q) (zden p) (zden q)))))
            -- term2: (nq·zb)·(zb'·zd) = (nq·zb')·(zb·zd), pure regrouping (one interchange)
            (zmulInterchange (qnum q) (zden p) (zden p') (zden q)))
          (trans
            (sym (zmulDistL (zmul (qnum p') (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p')) (zmul (zden p) (zden q))))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p') (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p'))) s end)
              (sym (qaddDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

qaddR : QPair -> Q -> Q is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    qlift QPair QRel Q
      (fn (q : QPair) is qin QPair QRel (qaddP p q) end)
      (fn (q : QPair) (q' : QPair) (r : QRel q q') is
        qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p q') (qaddRespR p q q' r)
      end)
  end
end

qadd : Q -> Q -> Q is
  qlift QPair QRel (Q -> Q) qaddR
    (fn (p : QPair) (p' : QPair) (r : QRel p p') is
      fn (z : Q) is
        qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qaddR p w) (qaddR p' w) end)
          (fn (q : QPair) is
            qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP p' q) (qaddRespL p p' q r)
          end)
          z
      end
    end)
end

-- THE FIELD LAW: COMMUTATIVITY OF ℚ ADDITION.  x + y = y + x.
-- On representatives, qaddP p q ~ qaddP q p: the numerators commute (the two summands
-- swap, zaddComm) and the denominators commute (zmulComm), lined up via the same
-- denominator-rewrite + cong2 assembly as qmulCommP.
qaddCommP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP q p) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (np·zd) (nq·zb)) (zden (qaddP q p))
    --     = zmul (zadd (nq·zb) (np·zd)) (zden (qaddP p q)).
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) s end)
        (qaddDenZ q p))
      (trans
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
          (zaddComm (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)))
          (zmulComm (zden q) (zden p)))
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden p)) (zmul (qnum p) (zden q))) s end)
          (sym (qaddDenZ p q))))
  end
end

qaddComm : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd x y) (qadd y x) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is (y : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd w y) (qadd y w) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) w) (qadd w (qin QPair QRel p)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p q) (qaddP q p) (qaddCommP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- Sanity: 1/2 + 1/2 = 1.  On representatives (1, succ 0) + (1, succ 0):
--   numerator = 1·2 + 1·2,  denominator index succ (qmulDen 1 1) = 2·2 = 4, i.e. 4/4-style;
-- it qsound-relates to 1/1 = qone. We pin the COMPUTED representative and prove it commutes.
qHalfPlusHalf : Q is qadd qHalf qHalf end

-- qadd qHalf qHalf computes to the explicit representative below (refl through the quotient).
qHalfSumRep : Q is
  qin QPair QRel
    (qpair (zadd (zmul zone (zden (qpair zone (succ zero))))
                 (zmul zone (zden (qpair zone (succ zero)))))
           (qmulDen (succ zero) (succ zero)))
end

qAddComputes : Eq Q (qadd qHalf qHalf) qHalfSumRep is
  refl (qadd qHalf qHalf)
end

-- Addition commutes on concrete rationals, by qaddComm.
qExAddComm : Eq Q (qadd qHalf qTwoOverOne) (qadd qTwoOverOne qHalf) is
  qaddComm qHalf qTwoOverOne
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 113 — CLOSING THE RING + FIELD STRUCTURE OF ℚ.
-- Everything above is the ch108 ℚ development (itself over the ch107 ℤ ring),
-- redeclared verbatim. Below: the remaining ring identities/axioms and the field
-- inverse. We first add the two ℤ lemmas ch108 omitted (zaddZeroR, zaddAssoc) and
-- a left-zero (zmulZeroL), then lift the ℚ ring laws through qind.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ℤ lemmas needed below (proven exactly as ch103/ch107, using ch108's Nat lemmas).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- LEFT ZERO: 0 · x = 0, from commutativity + zmulZeroR.
zmulZeroL : (x : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul zzero x) zzero is
  fn (x : Z) is
    trans (zmulComm zzero x) (zmulZeroR x)
  end
end

-- ADDITIVE RIGHT IDENTITY: z + 0 = z (ch103, restated with ch108's addZeroR).
zaddZeroR : (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd z zzero) z is
  fn (z : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zadd w zzero) w end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        qsound NatPair ZRel (padd p (npair zero zero)) p
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end) (addZeroR (fst p)))
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) s end) (sym (addZeroR (snd p)))))
      end)
      z
  end
end

-- ADDITIVE ASSOCIATIVITY: (x + y) + z = x + (y + z) (ch103, verbatim).
zaddAssoc : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z) ->
    Eq Z (zadd (zadd x y) z) (zadd x (zadd y z)) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel
      (fn (wx : Z) is (y : Z) -> (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd (zadd wx y) z) (zadd wx (zadd y z)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (wy : Z) is (z : Z) -> Eq Z (zadd (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) wy) z) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              fn (z : Z) is
                qind NatPair ZRel
                  (fn (wz : Z) is Eq Z (zadd (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) (qin NatPair ZRel q)) wz) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel p) (zadd (qin NatPair ZRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : NatPair) is
                    qsound NatPair ZRel
                      (padd (padd p q) r) (padd p (padd q r))
                      (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (add (snd p) (add (snd q) (snd r))) end)
                                (addAssoc (fst p) (fst q) (fst r)))
                        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (add (fst p) (add (fst q) (fst r))) s end)
                                (sym (addAssoc (snd p) (snd q) (snd r)))))
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING IDENTITY (×):  x · 1 = x.   qone = qin (1/1).
-- On a representative p: qmulP p (1,0) = ((np·1) / (zb·1)), and the QRel obligation
--   (np·1)·zb = np·(zb·1)  reduces — both sides to np·zb — by zmulOneR twice + qmulDenZ.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulOneRP : (p : QPair) -> QRel (qmulP p (qpair zone zero)) p is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) zone) (zden p) = zmul (qnum p) (zden (qmulP p (qpair zone zero)))
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden p) end) (zmulOneR (qnum p)))
      (sym
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (qmulDenZ p (qpair zone zero)))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (zmulOneR (zden p)))))
  end
end

qmulOneR : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul x qone) x is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qmul w qone) w end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p (qpair zone zero)) p (qmulOneRP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING IDENTITY (+):  x + 0 = x.   qzero = qin (0/1).
-- On p: qaddP p (0,0) numerator = (np·1) + (0·zb) = np; denominator = zb·1 = zb.
-- The QRel obligation np·zb = np·zb after the numerator collapses (zmulOneR + zmulZeroL
-- + zaddZeroR) and the denominator collapses (qaddDenZ + zmulOneR).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qaddZeroP : (p : QPair) -> QRel (qaddP p (qpair zzero zero)) p is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) zone) (zmul zzero (zden p))) (zden p)
    --     = zmul (qnum p) (zden (qaddP p (qpair zzero zero)))
    trans
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden p) end)
        (trans
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            (zmulOneR (qnum p))
            (zmulZeroL (zden p)))
          (zaddZeroR (qnum p))))
      (sym
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (qaddDenZ p (qpair zzero zero)))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (qnum p) s end) (zmulOneR (zden p)))))
  end
end

qaddZero : (x : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd x qzero) x is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel (fn (w : Q) is Eq Q (qadd w qzero) w end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        qsound QPair QRel (qaddP p (qpair zzero zero)) p (qaddZeroP p)
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING AXIOM (× ASSOCIATIVITY):  (x · y) · z = x · (y · z).
-- Triple qind. On representatives the numerators are zmulAssoc-equal and the
-- denominators (after qmulDenZ unfolds each product) are zmulAssoc-equal, so the
-- cross-multiplied QRel obligation is cong2Z (numerator-assoc) (denominator-assoc).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulAssocP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> QRel (qmulP (qmulP p q) r) (qmulP p (qmulP q r)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (qnum r)) (zden (qmulP p (qmulP q r)))
    --     = zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zmul (qnum q) (qnum r))) (zden (qmulP (qmulP p q) r))
    trans
      -- rewrite RHS denominator -> zmul (zden p) (zmul (zden q) (zden r))
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (qnum r)) s end)
        (trans (qmulDenZ p (qmulP q r))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end) (qmulDenZ q r))))
      (trans
        -- numerator-assoc + denominator (right-grouped -> left-grouped)
        (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
          (zmulAssoc (qnum p) (qnum q) (qnum r))
          (sym (zmulAssoc (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))))
        -- fold the (now left-grouped) denominator back to zden (qmulP (qmulP p q) r)
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zmul (qnum q) (qnum r))) s end)
          (sym (trans (qmulDenZ (qmulP p q) r)
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden r) end) (qmulDenZ p q))))))
  end
end

qmulAssoc : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qmul (qmul x y) z) (qmul x (qmul y z)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qmul wx y) z) (qmul wx (qmul y z)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wy) z) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qmul wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is Eq Q (qmul (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) wz) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qmul (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    qsound QPair QRel
                      (qmulP (qmulP p q) r) (qmulP p (qmulP q r))
                      (qmulAssocP p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING AXIOM (+ ASSOCIATIVITY):  (x + y) + z = x + (y + z).
-- The cross-multiplication obligation, with all denominators rewritten to products
-- by qaddDenZ, is the pure ℤ identity below in the six values a,b,c (numerators)
-- and x,y,z (denominators). Both numerators equal  a·y·z + b·x·z + c·x·y  (modulo
-- ℤ assoc/comm), and the two outer denominators are zmulAssoc-equal; assemble by cong2Z.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- numerator identity:  ((a·y + b·x)·z + c·(x·y))  =  (a·(y·z) + (b·z + c·y)·x).
qaddAssocNum : (a : Z) -> (b : Z) -> (c : Z) -> (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> (z : Z)
   -> Eq Z
        (zadd (zmul (zadd (zmul a y) (zmul b x)) z) (zmul c (zmul x y)))
        (zadd (zmul a (zmul y z)) (zmul (zadd (zmul b z) (zmul c y)) x)) is
  fn (a : Z) (b : Z) (c : Z) (x : Z) (y : Z) (z : Z) is
    trans
      -- distribute the first product:  (a·y + b·x)·z = (a·y)·z + (b·x)·z
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd s (zmul c (zmul x y)) end)
        (zmulDistL (zmul a y) (zmul b x) z))
      (trans
        -- reassociate the outer sum to the right
        (zaddAssoc (zmul (zmul a y) z) (zmul (zmul b x) z) (zmul c (zmul x y)))
        (trans
          -- term-by-term match against the RHS (after distributing its second product)
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
            -- T1: (a·y)·z = a·(y·z)
            (zmulAssoc a y z)
            (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
              -- T2: (b·x)·z = (b·z)·x
              (trans (zmulAssoc b x z)
                (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul b s end) (zmulComm x z))
                  (sym (zmulAssoc b z x))))
              -- T3: c·(x·y) = (c·y)·x
              (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul c s end) (zmulComm x y))
                (sym (zmulAssoc c y x)))))
          -- fold RHS second product back:  (b·z)·x + (c·y)·x = (b·z + c·y)·x
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zadd (zmul a (zmul y z)) s end)
            (sym (zmulDistL (zmul b z) (zmul c y) x)))))
  end
end

-- The full QRel obligation, threading qaddDenZ on each of the four denominator
-- occurrences and dispatching the resulting pure-ℤ identity by qaddAssocNum.
qaddAssocP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> QRel (qaddP (qaddP p q) r) (qaddP p (qaddP q r)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair) is
    trans
      -- (1a) rewrite the inner denominator zden (qaddP p q) -> zmul (zden p) (zden q)
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is
               zmul (zadd (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) (zden r))
                          (zmul (qnum r) s))
                    (zden (qaddP p (qaddP q r))) end)
        (qaddDenZ p q))
      (trans
        -- (1b) rewrite the outer right denominator -> zmul (zden p) (zmul (zden q) (zden r))
        (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                 zmul (zadd (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden q)) (zmul (qnum q) (zden p))) (zden r))
                            (zmul (qnum r) (zmul (zden p) (zden q))))
                      s end)
          (trans (qaddDenZ p (qaddP q r))
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end) (qaddDenZ q r))))
        (trans
          -- (2) the pure ℤ identity: numerator by qaddAssocNum, denominator by zmulAssoc
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end)
            (qaddAssocNum (qnum p) (qnum q) (qnum r) (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))
            (sym (zmulAssoc (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))))
          (trans
            -- (3a) fold zmul (zden q) (zden r) back to zden (qaddP q r) in the numerator
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                     zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) s)
                                (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q))) (zden p)))
                          (zmul (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) (zden r)) end)
              (sym (qaddDenZ q r)))
            -- (3b) fold the outer left denominator back to zden (qaddP (qaddP p q) r)
            (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                     zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum p) (zden (qaddP q r)))
                                (zmul (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q))) (zden p)))
                          s end)
              (sym (trans (qaddDenZ (qaddP p q) r)
                (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zden r) end) (qaddDenZ p q))))))))
  end
end

qaddAssoc : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd x y) z) (qadd x (qadd y z)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd wx y) z) (qadd wx (qadd y z)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qadd (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) wy) z) (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd wy z)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is Eq Q (qadd (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) wz) (qadd (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    qsound QPair QRel
                      (qaddP (qaddP p q) r) (qaddP p (qaddP q r))
                      (qaddAssocP p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- RING AXIOM (LEFT DISTRIBUTIVITY):  x · (y + z) = x·y + x·z.   The heaviest law.
-- After rewriting every denominator to a product, the cross-multiplication obligation
-- is the pure ℤ identity  numL · denR = numR · denL  where, crucially,
--   numR = zp · numL   and   denR = zp · denL
-- (the RHS carries an extra factor zp from the duplicated denominator), so the identity
-- collapses to a pure assoc/comm rearrangement once those two factorings are supplied.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- denominator factoring:  (zp·zq)·(zp·zr) = zp·(zp·(zq·zr)).
qmulDistDen : (zp : Z) -> (zq : Z) -> (zr : Z)
   -> Eq Z (zmul (zmul zp zq) (zmul zp zr)) (zmul zp (zmul zp (zmul zq zr))) is
  fn (zp : Z) (zq : Z) (zr : Z) is
    trans (zmulInterchange zp zq zp zr) (zmulAssoc zp zp (zmul zq zr))
  end
end

-- numerator factoring:
--   (np·nq)·(zp·zr) + (np·nr)·(zp·zq)  =  zp·(np·(nq·zr + nr·zq)).
qmulDistNum : (np : Z) -> (nq : Z) -> (nr : Z) -> (zp : Z) -> (zq : Z) -> (zr : Z)
   -> Eq Z
        (zadd (zmul (zmul np nq) (zmul zp zr)) (zmul (zmul np nr) (zmul zp zq)))
        (zmul zp (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq)))) is
  fn (np : Z) (nq : Z) (nr : Z) (zp : Z) (zq : Z) (zr : Z) is
    trans
      (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
        -- (np·nq)·(zp·zr) = zp·(np·(nq·zr))
        (trans (zmulInterchange np nq zp zr)
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul nq zr) end) (zmulComm np zp))
            (zmulAssoc zp np (zmul nq zr))))
        -- (np·nr)·(zp·zq) = zp·(np·(nr·zq))
        (trans (zmulInterchange np nr zp zq)
          (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul nr zq) end) (zmulComm np zp))
            (zmulAssoc zp np (zmul nr zq)))))
      -- fold:  zp·(np·(nq·zr)) + zp·(np·(nr·zq)) = zp·(np·(nq·zr + nr·zq))
      (sym
        (trans (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul zp s end)
                 (zmulDistR np (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq)))
          (zmulDistR zp (zmul np (zmul nq zr)) (zmul np (zmul nr zq)))))
  end
end

-- the pure-ℤ cross identity (everything in product-denominator form).
qmulDistCross : (np : Z) -> (nq : Z) -> (nr : Z) -> (zp : Z) -> (zq : Z) -> (zr : Z)
   -> Eq Z
        (zmul (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq)))
              (zmul (zmul zp zq) (zmul zp zr)))
        (zmul (zadd (zmul (zmul np nq) (zmul zp zr)) (zmul (zmul np nr) (zmul zp zq)))
              (zmul zp (zmul zq zr))) is
  fn (np : Z) (nq : Z) (nr : Z) (zp : Z) (zq : Z) (zr : Z) is
    trans
      -- denR = zp·denL
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq))) s end)
        (qmulDistDen zp zq zr))
      (trans
        -- numL·(zp·denL) = (numL·zp)·denL
        (sym (zmulAssoc (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq))) zp (zmul zp (zmul zq zr))))
        (trans
          -- (numL·zp)·denL = (zp·numL)·denL
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul zp (zmul zq zr)) end)
            (zmulComm (zmul np (zadd (zmul nq zr) (zmul nr zq))) zp))
          -- (zp·numL)·denL = numR·denL    (numR = zp·numL, reversed)
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul zp (zmul zq zr)) end)
            (sym (qmulDistNum np nq nr zp zq zr)))))
  end
end

-- The full QRel obligation for distributivity, threading qaddDenZ/qmulDenZ on the four
-- denominator occurrences and dispatching the pure-ℤ identity by qmulDistCross.
qmulDistRP : (p : QPair) -> (q : QPair) -> (r : QPair)
   -> QRel (qmulP p (qaddP q r)) (qaddP (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r)) is
  fn (p : QPair) (q : QPair) (r : QPair) is
    trans
      -- rewrite the LHS denominator  zden (qaddP (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r))
      --   -> zmul (zmul (zden p) (zden q)) (zmul (zden p) (zden r))
      (cong (fn (s : Z) is
               zmul (zmul (qnum p) (zadd (zmul (qnum q) (zden r)) (zmul (qnum r) (zden q)))) s end)
        (trans (qaddDenZ (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r))
          (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zmul u v end) (qmulDenZ p q) (qmulDenZ p r))))
      (trans
        -- the pure ℤ cross identity
        (qmulDistCross (qnum p) (qnum q) (qnum r) (zden p) (zden q) (zden r))
        (trans
          -- fold the numerator denominators back:  zmul (zden p) (zden r) -> zden (qmulP p r)
          --   and zmul (zden p) (zden q) -> zden (qmulP p q)
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zmul (zden p) (zmul (zden q) (zden r))) end)
            (cong2Z (fn (u : Z) (v : Z) is zadd u v end)
              (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) s end) (sym (qmulDenZ p r)))
              (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum r)) s end) (sym (qmulDenZ p q)))))
          -- fold the RHS (LHS-rep) denominator back to  zden (qmulP p (qaddP q r))
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is
                   zmul (zadd (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum q)) (zden (qmulP p r)))
                              (zmul (zmul (qnum p) (qnum r)) (zden (qmulP p q)))) s end)
            (sym (trans (qmulDenZ p (qaddP q r))
              (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end) (qaddDenZ q r)))))))
  end
end

qmulDistR : (x : Q) -> (y : Q) -> (z : Q)
   -> Eq Q (qmul x (qadd y z)) (qadd (qmul x y) (qmul x z)) is
  fn (x : Q) is
    qind QPair QRel
      (fn (wx : Q) is (y : Q) -> (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul wx (qadd y z)) (qadd (qmul wx y) (qmul wx z)) end)
      (fn (p : QPair) is
        fn (y : Q) is
          qind QPair QRel
            (fn (wy : Q) is (z : Q) -> Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd wy z)) (qadd (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wy) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) z)) end)
            (fn (q : QPair) is
              fn (z : Q) is
                qind QPair QRel
                  (fn (wz : Q) is Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qadd (qin QPair QRel q) wz)) (qadd (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qin QPair QRel q)) (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) wz)) end)
                  (fn (r : QPair) is
                    qsound QPair QRel
                      (qmulP p (qaddP q r)) (qaddP (qmulP p q) (qmulP p r))
                      (qmulDistRP p q r)
                  end)
                  z
              end
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CH113, PART II — THE MULTIPLICATIVE INVERSE (the field-defining piece).
--
-- ℚ is now a verified COMMUTATIVE RING (qmulOneR, qaddZero, qmulAssoc, qaddAssoc,
-- qmulDistR + ch108's qmulComm/qaddComm). The field structure adds the inverse on the
-- NONZERO rationals. The nonzero condition is essential: 1/0 is undefined.
--
-- A ℤ-nonzero predicate, representation-independent: z is nonzero iff z = 0 is absurd.
-- ============================================================================

-- Falsity, encoded impredicatively in Prop (no bottom data type in the listings; any Pi
-- into Prop is a Prop, so this stays in U via Prop <: U): the proposition proving everything.
Empty : Prop is (C : Prop) -> C end

-- z ≠ 0 in ℤ.  (For the field law the WITNESS is supplied by the caller; the law is
-- vacuous on z = 0, which is exactly why the inverse is undefined there.)
zNonzero : Z -> U is
  fn (z : Z) is Eq Z z zzero -> Empty end
end

-- A rational is nonzero iff its numerator is.
qNonzero : QPair -> U is
  fn (p : QPair) is zNonzero (qnum p) end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE INVERSE, on the DIRECTLY-REPRESENTABLE positive rationals.
-- Our representation  a / succ(b)  hardcodes a POSITIVE Nat denominator (the +1 trick),
-- so the inverse  succ(b) / a  is itself representable only when the numerator a is a
-- positive integer  zfrom (succ k)  (its reciprocal then has a positive Nat denominator
-- k).  On that subtype the inverse is TOTAL and the field law q · q⁻¹ = 1 holds with no
-- postulate:  qPos a b = succ(a)/succ(b),  qinvPos a b = succ(b)/succ(a).
-- (For a general nonzero z the inverse needs SIGN NORMALISATION — rewrite −n/d as n/−d
-- with a positive denominator — which is the next increment; see the closing note.)
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qPosP : Nat -> Nat -> QPair is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is qpair (zfrom (succ a)) b end
end

qPos : Nat -> Nat -> Q is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is qin QPair QRel (qPosP a b) end
end

-- the inverse representative: swap the (positive) numerator and denominator.
qinvPosP : Nat -> Nat -> QPair is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is qpair (zfrom (succ b)) a end
end

qinvPos : Nat -> Nat -> Q is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is qin QPair QRel (qinvPosP a b) end
end

-- positive numerators are nonzero — the predicate has a genuine inhabitant family.
-- (Stated; its proof needs a ℤ→Bool discriminator that respects ZRel, deferred with the
-- general inverse.  The field law below does NOT depend on it — positivity is structural.)
qPosNonzero : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> U is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is qNonzero (qPosP a b) end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE FIELD LAW (positive case):  qPos a b · qinvPos a b = 1.
-- On representatives:  (succ a / succ b) · (succ b / succ a) = (succ a · succ b)/(succ b · succ a).
-- The QRel obligation against 1/1 reduces to  succ a · succ b = succ b · succ a  (zmulComm),
-- after the spurious unit denominators collapse (zmulOneR/zmulOneL) and qmulDenZ folds
-- the product denominator.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulInvPosP : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> QRel (qmulP (qPosP a b) (qinvPosP a b)) (qpair zone zero) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (zfrom (succ a)) (zfrom (succ b))) zone
    --     = zmul zone (zden (qmulP (qPosP a b) (qinvPosP a b)))
    trans
      -- LHS: drop the unit denominator  X · 1 = X
      (zmulOneR (zmul (zfrom (succ a)) (zfrom (succ b))))
      (trans
        -- X = zmul (zfrom (succ b)) (zfrom (succ a))   [zmulComm]
        (zmulComm (zfrom (succ a)) (zfrom (succ b)))
        (trans
          -- zmul (zden p) (zden q) = zden (qmulP p q)   [sym qmulDenZ]
          (sym (qmulDenZ (qPosP a b) (qinvPosP a b)))
          -- zden (qmulP …) = zmul zone (zden (qmulP …))   [sym zmulOneL]
          (sym (zmulOneL (zden (qmulP (qPosP a b) (qinvPosP a b)))))))
  end
end

-- The field law, lifted to ℚ:  q · q⁻¹ = 1  for every positive rational q = succ a / succ b.
qmulInvPosR : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Q (qmul (qPos a b) (qinvPos a b)) qone is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    qsound QPair QRel (qmulP (qPosP a b) (qinvPosP a b)) (qpair zone zero)
      (qmulInvPosP a b)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Sanity: the field laws COMPUTE on concrete rationals.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- x · 1 = x on 1/2, by qmulOneR.
qExOneR : Eq Q (qmul qHalf qone) qHalf is qmulOneR qHalf end

-- x + 0 = x on 1/2, by qaddZero.
qExAddZero : Eq Q (qadd qHalf qzero) qHalf is qaddZero qHalf end

-- (2/3) · (3/2) = 1, via the multiplicative inverse.  2/3 = qPos 1 2, 3/2 = qinvPos 1 2.
qTwoThirds : Q is qPos (succ zero) (succ (succ zero)) end
qThreeHalves : Q is qinvPos (succ zero) (succ (succ zero)) end

qExInv : Eq Q (qmul qTwoThirds qThreeHalves) qone is
  qmulInvPosR (succ zero) (succ (succ zero))
end

-- associativity + distributivity on concrete rationals.
qExMulAssoc : Eq Q (qmul (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne) qHalf) (qmul qHalf (qmul qTwoOverOne qHalf)) is
  qmulAssoc qHalf qTwoOverOne qHalf
end

qExDist : Eq Q
    (qmul qHalf (qadd qHalf qTwoOverOne))
    (qadd (qmul qHalf qHalf) (qmul qHalf qTwoOverOne)) is
  qmulDistR qHalf qHalf qTwoOverOne
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 116 — THE ℤ ZERO-DISCRIMINATOR (closing ch113's documented blocker).
-- Everything above is the ch113 ring+field development (over ch108 ℚ / ch107 ℤ),
-- redeclared verbatim. Below: a decidable, REPRESENTATION-RESPECTING zero-test on ℤ,
-- and from it the proof of ch113's deferred `qPosNonzero`.
-- ============================================================================

-- Bool and decidable Nat equality, redeclared verbatim from ch85/ch75.
data Bool : U is
  true  : Bool
| false : Bool
end

-- DECIDABLE Nat equality (ch75/ch85, verbatim): zero=zero -> true, succ=succ recurse,
-- mixed -> false. The succ/succ case reduces DEFINITIONALLY: eqNat (succ k) (succ n) ~>
-- eqNat k n, and eqNat (succ k) zero ~> false, eqNat zero (succ n) ~> false.
eqNat : Nat -> Nat -> Bool is
  fn (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat -> Bool end)
      (fn (n : Nat) is
         NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Bool end) true (fn (j : Nat) (ih : Bool) is false end) n
       end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ihk : Nat -> Bool) is
         fn (n : Nat) is
           NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Bool end) false (fn (j : Nat) (ih : Bool) is ihk j end) n
         end
       end)
      m
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ADD-CANCELLATION LAWS of eqNat — the arithmetic facts the ZRel-respect proof needs.
-- LEFT cancel:  eqNat (k + a) (k + b) = eqNat a b.  Induction on k; the step is just the
-- IH because add (succ k) x ~> succ (add k x) and eqNat (succ _) (succ _) ~> eqNat _ _,
-- so both reductions are DEFINITIONAL and eqNat (add (succ k) a) (add (succ k) b) is
-- CONVERTIBLE to eqNat (add k a) (add k b).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
eqNatAddCancelL : (k : Nat) -> (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (eqNat (add k a) (add k b)) (eqNat a b) is
  fn (k : Nat) (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Bool (eqNat (add x a) (add x b)) (eqNat a b) end)
      (refl (eqNat a b))
      (fn (j : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (eqNat (add j a) (add j b)) (eqNat a b)) is ih end)
      k
  end
end

-- RIGHT cancel:  eqNat (a + k) (b + k) = eqNat a b, from left-cancel + commutativity.
eqNatAddCancelR : (k : Nat) -> (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (eqNat (add a k) (add b k)) (eqNat a b) is
  fn (k : Nat) (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is eqNat u v end) (addComm a k) (addComm b k))
      (eqNatAddCancelL k a b)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE CRUX: eqNat respects ZRel.  Given a + d = c + b, prove eqNat a b = eqNat c d.
--   eqNat a b                                       [start]
--     = eqNat (a + d) (b + d)         [sym eqNatAddCancelR d a b]
--     = eqNat (c + b) (b + d)         [hypothesis a + d = c + b, in the first arg]
--     = eqNat (b + c) (b + d)         [addComm c b, in the first arg]
--     = eqNat c d                     [eqNatAddCancelL b c d]
-- (a + d) is zero-as-an-integer testimony lined up so the cancellation laws fire.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
eqNatRespects : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (add a d) (add c b) -> Eq Bool (eqNat a b) (eqNat c d) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat) (r : Eq Nat (add a d) (add c b)) is
    trans
      (sym (eqNatAddCancelR d a b))
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is eqNat s (add b d) end) r)
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is eqNat s (add b d) end) (addComm c b))
          (eqNatAddCancelL b c d)))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE DISCRIMINATOR.  zIsZero : Z -> Bool.  On a rep (a, b) (denoting a − b), the integer
-- is zero iff a = b iff eqNat a b. We lift  λ(a,b). eqNat (fst p) (snd p)  over ZRel:
-- the respect obligation is exactly eqNatRespects on (fst p, snd p, fst p', snd p'),
-- since ZRel p p' = Eq Nat (add (fst p) (snd p')) (add (fst p') (snd p)).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
zIsZero : Z -> Bool is
  qlift NatPair ZRel Bool
    (fn (p : NatPair) is eqNat (fst p) (snd p) end)
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      eqNatRespects (fst p) (snd p) (fst p') (snd p') r
    end)
end

-- zIsZero 0 = true.  zzero = qin (0, 0); qlift's ι-rule reduces zIsZero (qin (0,0)) to
-- eqNat 0 0 = true, all definitional — refl.
zIsZeroZero : Eq Bool (zIsZero zzero) true is refl true end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- BOOL DISCRIMINATION: true ≠ false.  Standard subst-into-a-Prop-motive: a predicate
-- that is an inhabited Prop on `true` and Empty on `false`; transport the inhabitant
-- of IsTrue true along true = false to land in IsTrue false = Empty.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Top : Prop is (C : Prop) -> C -> C end
topI : Top is fn (C : Prop) (c : C) is c end end

IsTrue : Bool -> Prop is
  fn (b : Bool) is BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Prop end) Top Empty b end
end

boolTrueNeFalse : Eq Bool true false -> Empty is
  fn (e : Eq Bool true false) is
    subst Bool true false e (fn (b : Bool) is IsTrue b end) topI
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- CORRECTNESS: zIsZero z = false ⟹ z is nonzero.  If z were 0 then zIsZero z = zIsZero 0
-- = true (cong + zIsZeroZero), contradicting zIsZero z = false (boolTrueNeFalse).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
zIsZeroFalseNonzero : (z : Z) -> Eq Bool (zIsZero z) false -> zNonzero z is
  fn (z : Z) (h : Eq Bool (zIsZero z) false) is
    fn (e : Eq Z z zzero) is
      boolTrueNeFalse
        (trans
          (sym (trans (cong zIsZero e) zIsZeroZero))
          h)
    end
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- CLOSING CH113'S BLOCKER:  qPosNonzero a b — the positive numerator succ a / succ b is
-- genuinely nonzero.  qPosP a b has numerator zfrom (succ a) = qin (succ a, 0), so
-- zIsZero (zfrom (succ a)) reduces (qlift ι) to eqNat (succ a) 0 = false DEFINITIONALLY
-- (the succ/zero arm). zIsZeroFalseNonzero on (refl false) discharges it.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qPosNonzeroPf : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> qPosNonzero a b is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    zIsZeroFalseNonzero (zfrom (succ a)) (refl false)
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Sanity: the discriminator COMPUTES and discriminates.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-- zIsZero 0 = true, computing through the quotient (refl).
zExIsZeroTrue : Eq Bool (zIsZero zzero) true is refl true end

-- zIsZero (−2) = false: zexRight = qin (0, 3) (denoting −3); zIsZero reduces to
-- eqNat 0 3 = false. Negative integers are discriminated correctly, computing.
zExIsZeroNegFalse : Eq Bool (zIsZero zexRight) false is refl false end

-- zIsZero 2 = false (zexLeft = qin (2, 0)): eqNat 2 0 = false, computing.
zExIsZeroPosFalse : Eq Bool (zIsZero zexLeft) false is refl false end

-- The deferred lemma, instantiated: 2/3's numerator (= zfrom 2 = succ 1) is nonzero.
qExPosNonzero : qPosNonzero (succ zero) (succ (succ zero)) is
  qPosNonzeroPf (succ zero) (succ (succ zero))
end

-- ============================================================================
-- CHAPTER 117 — THE FULLY-GENERAL MULTIPLICATIVE INVERSE.  ℚ as a verified FIELD.
-- Everything above is the ch116 development (ch113 ring+field over ch108 ℚ / ch107 ℤ,
-- plus the zIsZero zero-discriminator), redeclared verbatim. Below: the magnitude/sign
-- extraction Z → (Nat, Bool) respecting ZRel, the integer negation `zneg`, and the
-- GENERAL inverse qinv with its field law qmulInvR — q · q⁻¹ = 1 for ANY nonzero q.
-- ============================================================================

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- TRUNCATED NAT SUBTRACTION `monus` (m − n, floored at 0) and its laws.  monus recurses
-- on the SECOND argument: monus m 0 = m, monus m (succ k) = pred (monus m k).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pred : Nat -> Nat is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat end) zero (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat) is k end) n
  end
end

monus : Nat -> Nat -> Nat is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat end) m (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat) is pred ih end) n
  end
end

-- monus m (succ k) ~> pred (monus m k) and monus m zero ~> m are DEFINITIONAL.
-- monus zero n = zero, by induction on n (pred zero = zero definitionally).
monusZeroL : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (monus zero n) zero is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (monus zero x) zero end)
      (refl zero)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (monus zero k) zero) is
         cong pred ih
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- monus (succ m) (succ n) = monus m n, by induction on n.
--   n = 0:    monus (succ m) (succ 0) = pred (monus (succ m) 0) = pred (succ m) = m
--             and monus m 0 = m. (definitional)
--   n = succ: monus (succ m)(succ(succ k)) = pred (monus (succ m)(succ k)) = pred (monus m k)
--             [IH] and monus m (succ k) = pred (monus m k). (cong pred ih)
monusSuccSucc : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (monus (succ m) (succ n)) (monus m n) is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (monus (succ m) (succ x)) (monus m x) end)
      (refl m)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (monus (succ m) (succ k)) (monus m k)) is
         cong pred ih
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- SHIFT-CANCELLATION:  monus (add a c) (add b c) = monus a b, by induction on c, reusing
-- monusSuccSucc (add x (succ c) ~> succ (add x c) by addSuccR).
monusShift : (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat) -> (c : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (monus (add a c) (add b c)) (monus a b) is
  fn (a : Nat) (b : Nat) (c : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Nat (monus (add a x) (add b x)) (monus a b) end)
      -- c = 0: add a 0 = a, add b 0 = b (addZeroR), so monus (add a 0)(add b 0) = monus a b.
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is monus u v end) (addZeroR a) (addZeroR b))
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Nat (monus (add a k) (add b k)) (monus a b)) is
         -- monus (add a (succ k)) (add b (succ k))
         --   = monus (succ (add a k)) (succ (add b k))   [addSuccR ×2]
         --   = monus (add a k) (add b k)                 [monusSuccSucc]
         --   = monus a b                                 [IH]
         trans
           (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is monus u v end) (addSuccR a k) (addSuccR b k))
           (trans (monusSuccSucc (add a k) (add b k)) ih)
       end)
      c
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ORDER, on Nat (ch83 verbatim): lte a b = a <= b, recursing on the first argument.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
lte : Nat -> Nat -> Bool is
  fn (a : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Nat -> Bool end)
      (fn (n : Nat) is true end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Nat -> Bool) is
         fn (n : Nat) is
           NatElim (fn (y : Nat) is Bool end)
             false
             (fn (m : Nat) (ih2 : Bool) is ih m end)
             n
         end
       end)
      a
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE MAGNITUDE  zMag : Z -> Nat  — the absolute value |m − n| of a rep (m, n).
-- Defined as add (monus m n) (monus n m): for (m,n), at most one of monus m n, monus n m
-- is nonzero (the other is 0), so the sum is exactly |m − n|, with no case-split needed.
-- ============================================================================

-- magnitude on a representative.
pMag : NatPair -> Nat is
  fn (p : NatPair) is add (monus (fst p) (snd p)) (monus (snd p) (fst p)) end
end

-- THE CRUX: pMag respects ZRel.  Given (m,n) ~ (c,d), i.e. add m d = add c n, show
-- add (monus m n) (monus n m) = add (monus c d) (monus d c).  Each term shifts:
--   monus m n = monus (add m d) (add n d)   [sym monusShift, by d]
--             = monus (add c n) (add n d)   [hypothesis add m d = add c n]
--             = monus (add c n) (add d n)   [addComm n d in 2nd arg]
--             = monus c d                   [monusShift, by n]
-- and symmetrically monus n m = monus d c (the same with the hypothesis reversed/commuted).
zMagRespectsTerm : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> (c : Nat) -> (d : Nat)
   -> Eq Nat (add m d) (add c n) -> Eq Nat (monus m n) (monus c d) is
  fn (m : Nat) (n : Nat) (c : Nat) (d : Nat) (r : Eq Nat (add m d) (add c n)) is
    trans
      (sym (monusShift m n d))
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is monus s (add n d) end) r)
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is monus (add c n) s end) (addComm n d))
          (monusShift c d n)))
  end
end

zMagRespects : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> ZRel p p' -> Eq Nat (pMag p) (pMag p') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    -- ZRel p p' = add (fst p) (snd p') = add (fst p') (snd p).
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      -- monus (fst p) (snd p) = monus (fst p') (snd p'), via r directly.
      (zMagRespectsTerm (fst p) (snd p) (fst p') (snd p') r)
      -- monus (snd p) (fst p) = monus (snd p') (fst p'), via the commuted hypothesis:
      --   add (snd p) (fst p') = add (snd p') (fst p)  (addComm of both sides of r).
      (zMagRespectsTerm (snd p) (fst p) (snd p') (fst p')
        (trans (addComm (snd p) (fst p'))
          (trans (sym r) (addComm (fst p) (snd p')))))
  end
end

zMag : Z -> Nat is
  qlift NatPair ZRel Nat
    (fn (p : NatPair) is pMag p end)
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is zMagRespects p p' r end)
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE SIGN  zSign : Z -> Bool  — true iff the integer is ≤ 0 (m ≤ n on a rep (m,n)).
-- This is the "use the negated branch of the inverse" test: true ⟹ reconstruct a as
-- zneg (zfrom (zMag a)); false ⟹ reconstruct a as zfrom (zMag a). (At a = 0 the test is
-- true and the reconstruction still holds — strictness is not needed.)
-- ============================================================================
pSign : NatPair -> Bool is
  fn (p : NatPair) is lte (fst p) (snd p) end
end

-- lte respects add-cancellation the same way eqNat does: lte (k+a)(k+b) = lte a b
-- (induction on k; the step is the IH since lte (succ _)(succ _) ~> lte _ _ and
-- add (succ k) x ~> succ (add k x)), and the right version by addComm.
lteAddCancelL : (k : Nat) -> (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte (add k a) (add k b)) (lte a b) is
  fn (k : Nat) (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (add x a) (add x b)) (lte a b) end)
      (refl (lte a b))
      (fn (j : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (lte (add j a) (add j b)) (lte a b)) is ih end)
      k
  end
end

lteAddCancelR : (k : Nat) -> (a : Nat) -> (b : Nat)
   -> Eq Bool (lte (add a k) (add b k)) (lte a b) is
  fn (k : Nat) (a : Nat) (b : Nat) is
    trans
      (cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is lte u v end) (addComm a k) (addComm b k))
      (lteAddCancelL k a b)
  end
end

-- pSign respects ZRel.  Given add m d = add c n, show lte m n = lte c d.
--   lte m n = lte (add m d) (add n d)   [sym lteAddCancelR d]
--           = lte (add c n) (add n d)   [hypothesis add m d = add c n, 1st arg]
--           = lte (add c n) (add d n)   [addComm n d, 2nd arg]
--           = lte c d                   [lteAddCancelR n]
zSignRespects : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> ZRel p p' -> Eq Bool (pSign p) (pSign p') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    trans
      (sym (lteAddCancelR (snd p') (fst p) (snd p)))
      (trans
        (cong (fn (s : Nat) is lte s (add (snd p) (snd p')) end) r)
        (trans
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is lte (add (fst p') (snd p)) s end) (addComm (snd p) (snd p')))
          (lteAddCancelR (snd p) (fst p') (snd p'))))
  end
end

zSign : Z -> Bool is
  qlift NatPair ZRel Bool
    (fn (p : NatPair) is pSign p end)
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is zSignRespects p p' r end)
end

-- ============================================================================
-- INTEGER NEGATION  zneg : Z -> Z  — lift pneg (swap the components of a rep).
-- ============================================================================
pnegRespects : (p : NatPair) -> (p' : NatPair) -> ZRel p p' -> ZRel (pneg p) (pneg p') is
  fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
    -- ZRel (pneg p) (pneg p') = add (snd p) (fst p') = add (snd p') (fst p).
    trans (addComm (snd p) (fst p'))
      (trans (sym r) (addComm (fst p) (snd p')))
  end
end

zneg : Z -> Z is
  qlift NatPair ZRel Z
    (fn (p : NatPair) is qin NatPair ZRel (pneg p) end)
    (fn (p : NatPair) (p' : NatPair) (r : ZRel p p') is
      qsound NatPair ZRel (pneg p) (pneg p') (pnegRespects p p' r)
    end)
end

-- (zneg x) · (zneg y) = x · y.  On reps, pmul (pneg p)(pneg q) and pmul p q have equal
-- components up to addComm (negation swaps which products land in the fst/snd slot).
zNegMulNegP : (p : NatPair) -> (q : NatPair) -> ZRel (pmul (pneg p) (pneg q)) (pmul p q) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (q : NatPair) is
    -- pmul (pneg p)(pneg q) = (snd p · snd q + fst p · fst q, snd p · fst q + fst p · snd q)
    -- pmul p q              = (fst p · fst q + snd p · snd q, fst p · snd q + snd p · fst q)
    -- ZRel obligation: fst(LHS) + snd(RHS) = fst(RHS) + snd(LHS), each side regrouped by addComm.
    cong2 (fn (u : Nat) (v : Nat) is add u v end)
      (addComm (mul (snd p) (snd q)) (mul (fst p) (fst q)))
      (addComm (mul (fst p) (snd q)) (mul (snd p) (fst q)))
  end
end

zNegMulNeg : (x : Z) -> (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zneg x) (zneg y)) (zmul x y) is
  fn (x : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is (y : Z) -> Eq Z (zmul (zneg w) (zneg y)) (zmul w y) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (y : Z) is
          qind NatPair ZRel
            (fn (w : Z) is Eq Z (zmul (zneg (qin NatPair ZRel p)) (zneg w)) (zmul (qin NatPair ZRel p) w) end)
            (fn (q : NatPair) is
              qsound NatPair ZRel (pmul (pneg p) (pneg q)) (pmul p q) (zNegMulNegP p q)
            end)
            y
        end
      end)
      x
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- MAGNITUDE RECONSTRUCTION.  For a NONZERO z, z = ± zfrom (zMag z): positive z equals
-- zfrom (zMag z), negative z equals zneg (zfrom (zMag z)). We prove the rep-level facts:
--   pMagPosP: when fst p >= snd p, qin p = zfrom (pMag p)
--   pMagNegP: when fst p <= snd p, qin p = zneg (zfrom (pMag p))
-- on ALL reps via the SAME ZRel obligation, because monus floors at zero — the "wrong"
-- monus is 0 and pMag p collapses to the genuine one-sided difference. We do NOT need the
-- order hypothesis to STATE the obligation; the floor makes it hold for every rep.
-- ============================================================================

-- KEY ARITHMETIC: for every m, n,  add n (add (monus m n) (monus n m)) = add m (add (monus n m) (monus m n)).
-- Both sides equal max(m,n) + |m−n| ... but we avoid case analysis. We instead prove the
-- two reconstruction relations directly as ZRel obligations using the identity
--   add n (monus m n) = add m (monus n m)               (the symmetric monus law, monusAdd)
-- which holds for ALL m, n (it is max m n on both sides), proven by double induction.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- monusAdd: add n (monus m n) = add m (monus n m)  (= max m n), by induction on m then n.
monusAdd : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n (monus m n)) (add m (monus n m)) is
  fn (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n (monus x n)) (add x (monus n x)) end)
      -- m = 0: add n (monus 0 n) = add n 0 = n [monusZeroL, addZeroR];
      --        add 0 (monus n 0) = monus n 0 = n. So both = n.
      (fn (n : Nat) is
         trans
           (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add n s end) (monusZeroL n)) (addZeroR n))
           (refl n)
       end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : (n : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add n (monus k n)) (add k (monus n k))) is
         fn (n : Nat) is
           NatElim (fn (y : Nat) is Eq Nat (add y (monus (succ k) y)) (add (succ k) (monus y (succ k))) end)
             -- n = 0: add 0 (monus (succ k) 0) = succ k; add (succ k) (monus 0 (succ k)) =
             --        add (succ k) 0 = succ k [monusZeroL, addZeroR].
             (sym (trans (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (succ k) s end) (monusZeroL (succ k)))
                     (addZeroR (succ k))))
             (fn (j : Nat) (ihj : Eq Nat (add j (monus (succ k) j)) (add (succ k) (monus j (succ k)))) is
                -- n = succ j: LHS add (succ j) (monus (succ k)(succ j)) = succ (add j (monus k j))
                --   [addSuccR? no — add (succ j) x ~> succ (add j x); monusSuccSucc].
                -- RHS add (succ k) (monus (succ j)(succ k)) = succ (add k (monus j k)) similarly.
                -- The goal is succ (add j (monus k j)) = succ (add k (monus j k)) = cong succ (ih j).
                trans
                  (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (succ j) s end) (monusSuccSucc k j))
                  (trans
                    (cong succ (ih j))
                    (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (succ k) s end) (sym (monusSuccSucc j k))))
              end)
             n
         end
       end)
      m
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE SIGNED INVERSE — directly, WITHOUT a global magnitude reconstruction.
--
-- The deep difficulty avoided: reconstructing `a = ± zfrom (zMag a)` needs a sign
-- case-split that monus does not deliver definitionally. We sidestep it: instead of
-- choosing the inverse's numerator/denominator from zMag/zSign of the NUMERATOR a, we
-- read them off the REPRESENTATIVE (m, n) of a = qin (m, n) — both monus differences are
-- present, and the field-law obligation is a PURE Nat semiring identity in m, n (and the
-- denominator), needing only monusAdd, NOT the order. This is the key simplification that
-- makes the GENERAL inverse computable with the algebra already in hand.
--
-- For p = qpair a denN with a = qin (am, an):  the old denominator is sb = zfrom (succ
-- denN). The inverse is sb / a. We represent it as the QPair
--   qinvP p = qpair  (signedDen)  (magPred a)
-- where magPred a = pred (zMag a) (so succ (magPred a) = zMag a when a ≠ 0), and the
-- numerator carries the sign:
--   signedDen = if zSign a then zneg sb else sb.
-- Then zden (qinvP p) = zfrom (succ (magPred a)). With a ≠ 0 (the hypothesis), zMag a is a
-- successor, so zfrom (succ (magPred a)) = zfrom (zMag a). The field law then needs
--   zmul a signedDen = zmul sb (zfrom (zMag a)),
-- which splits on zSign a and uses the rep-level reconstruction of a · (zfrom (zMag a))
-- proven below (no global order lemma — both monus terms participate).
-- ============================================================================

-- magPred z = pred (zMag z); succ (magPred z) = zMag z exactly when zMag z is a successor,
-- i.e. when z ≠ 0. We prove that conditional next.
magPred : Z -> Nat is fn (z : Z) is pred (zMag z) end end

-- zNonzero z gives zMag z ≠ 0, hence succ (magPred z) = zMag z.  Strategy: a Nat n is
-- either zero or a successor; if zMag z = zero then z = zfrom 0 = zzero (rep reconstruction
-- pZeroFromMagZero), contradicting nonzeroness, so zMag z = succ (pred (zMag z)).
-- We discriminate via eqNat (zMag z) zero and the BoolElim-into-Prop trick.

-- succPredId: for n ≠ 0 (i.e. eqNat n zero = false), succ (pred n) = n. By NatElim:
--   n = 0:    eqNat 0 0 = true, so the hypothesis (true = false) is absurd (Empty -> anything).
--   n = succ k: succ (pred (succ k)) = succ k, refl (independent of the hypothesis).
succPredId : (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (eqNat n zero) false -> Eq Nat (succ (pred n)) n is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Bool (eqNat x zero) false -> Eq Nat (succ (pred x)) x end)
      (fn (h : Eq Bool (eqNat zero zero) false) is
         -- eqNat 0 0 ~> true, so h : true = false, absurd.
         boolTrueNeFalse h (Eq Nat (succ (pred zero)) zero)
       end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (eqNat k zero) false -> Eq Nat (succ (pred k)) k) is
         fn (h : Eq Bool (eqNat (succ k) zero) false) is refl (succ k) end
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Nat zero-discrimination (the additive analog of boolTrueNeFalse).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
TopN : Prop is (C : Prop) -> C -> C end
topNI : TopN is fn (C : Prop) (c : C) is c end end

IsZeroN : Nat -> Prop is
  fn (n : Nat) is NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Prop end) TopN (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Prop) is Empty end) n end
end

-- succ k = zero is absurd.
succNeZero : (k : Nat) -> Eq Nat (succ k) zero -> Empty is
  fn (k : Nat) (e : Eq Nat (succ k) zero) is
    subst Nat zero (succ k) (sym e) (fn (n : Nat) is IsZeroN n end) topNI
  end
end

-- add x y = 0 ⟹ x = 0 (otherwise x = succ k makes add (succ k) y = succ (...) ≠ 0).
addZeroSplitL : (x : Nat) -> (y : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add x y) zero -> Eq Nat x zero is
  fn (x : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (w : Nat) is (y : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add w y) zero -> Eq Nat w zero end)
      (fn (y : Nat) (e : Eq Nat (add zero y) zero) is refl zero end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : (y : Nat) -> Eq Nat (add k y) zero -> Eq Nat k zero) is
         fn (y : Nat) (e : Eq Nat (add (succ k) y) zero) is
           -- add (succ k) y ~> succ (add k y), so e : succ (add k y) = zero — absurd.
           succNeZero (add k y) e (Eq Nat (succ k) zero)
         end
       end)
      x
  end
end

-- eqNat n zero = true ⟹ n = zero (decidable equality soundness at zero).
eqNatZeroSound : (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (eqNat n zero) true -> Eq Nat n zero is
  fn (n : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (x : Nat) is Eq Bool (eqNat x zero) true -> Eq Nat x zero end)
      (fn (h : Eq Bool (eqNat zero zero) true) is refl zero end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : Eq Bool (eqNat k zero) true -> Eq Nat k zero) is
         -- eqNat (succ k) zero ~> false, so h : false = true — absurd.
         fn (h : Eq Bool (eqNat (succ k) zero) true) is
           boolTrueNeFalse (sym h) (Eq Nat (succ k) zero)
         end
       end)
      n
  end
end

-- a Bool that cannot be true is false.
notTrueFalse : (b : Bool) -> (Eq Bool b true -> Empty) -> Eq Bool b false is
  fn (b : Bool) is
    BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is (Eq Bool x true -> Empty) -> Eq Bool x false end)
      (fn (h : Eq Bool true true -> Empty) is h (refl true) (Eq Bool true false) end)
      (fn (h : Eq Bool false true -> Empty) is refl false end)
      b
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- ORDER ↔ monus facts.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- m ≤ n ⟹ monus m n = 0, by double induction (m outer, n inner).
monusLteZero : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte m n) true -> Eq Nat (monus m n) zero is
  fn (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (w : Nat) is (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte w n) true -> Eq Nat (monus w n) zero end)
      -- m = 0: monus 0 n = 0 (monusZeroL), independent of the hypothesis.
      (fn (n : Nat) (h : Eq Bool (lte zero n) true) is monusZeroL n end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k n) true -> Eq Nat (monus k n) zero) is
         fn (n : Nat) is
           NatElim (fn (y : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (succ k) y) true -> Eq Nat (monus (succ k) y) zero end)
             -- n = 0: lte (succ k) 0 ~> false, so h : false = true is absurd.
             (fn (h : Eq Bool (lte (succ k) zero) true) is
                boolTrueNeFalse (sym h) (Eq Nat (monus (succ k) zero) zero)
              end)
             -- n = succ j: lte (succ k)(succ j) ~> lte k j; monus (succ k)(succ j) = monus k j.
             (fn (j : Nat) (ihy : Eq Bool (lte (succ k) j) true -> Eq Nat (monus (succ k) j) zero) is
                fn (h : Eq Bool (lte (succ k) (succ j)) true) is
                  trans (monusSuccSucc k j) (ih j h)
                end
              end)
             n
         end
       end)
      m
  end
end

-- lte m n = false ⟹ lte n m = true (the totality flip), by double induction.
lteFalseFlip : (m : Nat) -> (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte m n) false -> Eq Bool (lte n m) true is
  fn (m : Nat) is
    NatElim (fn (w : Nat) is (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte w n) false -> Eq Bool (lte n w) true end)
      -- m = 0: lte 0 n ~> true, so h : true = false is absurd.
      (fn (n : Nat) (h : Eq Bool (lte zero n) false) is
         boolTrueNeFalse h (Eq Bool (lte n zero) true)
       end)
      (fn (k : Nat) (ih : (n : Nat) -> Eq Bool (lte k n) false -> Eq Bool (lte n k) true) is
         fn (n : Nat) is
           NatElim (fn (y : Nat) is Eq Bool (lte (succ k) y) false -> Eq Bool (lte y (succ k)) true end)
             -- n = 0: lte 0 (succ k) ~> true.
             (fn (h : Eq Bool (lte (succ k) zero) false) is refl true end)
             -- n = succ j: lte (succ k)(succ j) ~> lte k j; goal lte (succ j)(succ k) ~> lte j k = IH.
             (fn (j : Nat) (ihy : Eq Bool (lte (succ k) j) false -> Eq Bool (lte j (succ k)) true) is
                fn (h : Eq Bool (lte (succ k) (succ j)) false) is ih j h end
              end)
             n
         end
       end)
      m
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE FULL RECONSTRUCTION (no order):  qin (m,n) ~ qin (monus m n, monus n m), for ALL
-- reps. The ZRel obligation  add m (monus n m) = add (monus m n) n  is exactly monusAdd
-- (commuted). This is the engine of the signed reconstruction: only one of the two monus
-- components is nonzero, and which one is the sign.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pMagFull : (p : NatPair) -> ZRel p (npair (monus (fst p) (snd p)) (monus (snd p) (fst p))) is
  fn (p : NatPair) is
    -- Goal: add (fst p) (monus (snd p) (fst p)) = add (monus (fst p) (snd p)) (snd p).
    trans
      (sym (monusAdd (fst p) (snd p)))
      (addComm (snd p) (monus (fst p) (snd p)))
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- zMag z = 0 ⟹ z = 0.  At rep level: pMag p = 0 forces both monus components to 0
-- (addZeroSplitL), so monusAdd collapses to fst p = snd p, hence qin p ~ (0,0).
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
pMagZeroZRel : (p : NatPair) -> Eq Nat (pMag p) zero -> ZRel p (npair zero zero) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (h : Eq Nat (pMag p) zero) is
    -- from h: monus (fst p)(snd p) = 0 and monus (snd p)(fst p) = 0.
    -- monusAdd (fst p)(snd p): add (snd p)(monus (fst,snd)) = add (fst p)(monus (snd,fst)).
    -- both monus collapse to 0 (addZeroR), giving snd p = fst p, so fst p = snd p by sym.
    -- ZRel obligation: add (fst p) zero = snd p (since add zero (snd p) ~> snd p).
    trans
      (addZeroR (fst p))
      -- fst p = snd p:
      (sym
        (trans
          -- snd p = add (snd p) (monus (fst p)(snd p))   [sym addZeroR + monus0]
          (trans
            (sym (addZeroR (snd p)))
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (snd p) s end)
              (sym (addZeroSplitL (monus (fst p) (snd p)) (monus (snd p) (fst p)) h))))
          (trans
            -- = add (fst p) (monus (snd p)(fst p))        [monusAdd]
            (monusAdd (fst p) (snd p))
            -- = add (fst p) zero = fst p                  [monus0 + addZeroR]
            (trans
              (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) s end)
                (addZeroSplitL (monus (snd p) (fst p)) (monus (fst p) (snd p))
                  (trans (addComm (monus (snd p) (fst p)) (monus (fst p) (snd p))) h)))
              (addZeroR (fst p))))))
  end
end

zMagZeroImpliesZero : (z : Z) -> Eq Nat (zMag z) zero -> Eq Z z zzero is
  fn (z : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Nat (zMag w) zero -> Eq Z w zzero end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (h : Eq Nat (zMag (qin NatPair ZRel p)) zero) is
          qsound NatPair ZRel p (npair zero zero) (pMagZeroZRel p h)
        end
      end)
      z
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE NONZERO ⟹ MAGNITUDE-IS-A-SUCCESSOR link:  succ (magPred z) = zMag z for z ≠ 0.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
magNotZero : (z : Z) -> zNonzero z -> Eq Bool (eqNat (zMag z) zero) false is
  fn (z : Z) (nz : zNonzero z) is
    notTrueFalse (eqNat (zMag z) zero)
      (fn (e : Eq Bool (eqNat (zMag z) zero) true) is
         nz (zMagZeroImpliesZero z (eqNatZeroSound (zMag z) e))
       end)
  end
end

magPredSucc : (z : Z) -> zNonzero z -> Eq Nat (succ (magPred z)) (zMag z) is
  fn (z : Z) (nz : zNonzero z) is
    succPredId (zMag z) (magNotZero z nz)
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE SIGNED RECONSTRUCTIONS (rep level).
--   pSign p = false (¬ fst≤snd, so snd≤fst):  qin p = zfrom (pMag p)        — nonnegative.
--   pSign p = true  (fst≤snd):                qin p = zneg (zfrom (pMag p)) — nonpositive.
-- Each is a single qsound; the ZRel obligation uses the vanishing of the "wrong" monus
-- (monusLteZero on the order side delivered by lteFalseFlip / the hypothesis).
-- ============================================================================

-- POSITIVE side.  msn := monus (snd p)(fst p) = 0 (since snd p ≤ fst p).
-- ZRel p (npair (pMag p) zero):  add (fst p) zero = add (pMag p) (snd p), and pMag p =
-- add (monus(fst,snd)) msn = monus(fst,snd) here.
zReconPosP : (p : NatPair) -> Eq Bool (pSign p) false -> ZRel p (npair (pMag p) zero) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (hs : Eq Bool (lte (fst p) (snd p)) false) is
    -- msn0 : monus (snd p)(fst p) = 0
    trans
      (addZeroR (fst p))
      (trans
        -- fst p = add (fst p) (monus (snd p)(fst p))   [sym addZeroR + sym msn0]
        (trans
          (sym (addZeroR (fst p)))
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) s end)
            (sym (monusLteZero (snd p) (fst p) (lteFalseFlip (fst p) (snd p) hs)))))
        -- = add (monus(fst,snd)) (snd p)               [pMagFull obligation]
        -- = add (add (monus(fst,snd)) msn) (snd p) = add (pMag p) (snd p)   [msn = 0, re-expand]
        (trans
          (pMagFull p)
          (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end)
            (trans
              (sym (addZeroR (monus (fst p) (snd p))))
              (cong (fn (t : Nat) is add (monus (fst p) (snd p)) t end)
                (sym (monusLteZero (snd p) (fst p) (lteFalseFlip (fst p) (snd p) hs))))))))
  end
end

zReconPos : (z : Z) -> Eq Bool (zSign z) false -> Eq Z z (zfrom (zMag z)) is
  fn (z : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Bool (zSign w) false -> Eq Z w (zfrom (zMag w)) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (hs : Eq Bool (zSign (qin NatPair ZRel p)) false) is
          qsound NatPair ZRel p (npair (pMag p) zero) (zReconPosP p hs)
        end
      end)
      z
  end
end

-- NEGATIVE side.  mfn := monus (fst p)(snd p) = 0 (since fst p ≤ snd p).
-- zneg (zfrom (pMag p)) = qin (pneg (npair (pMag p) zero)) = qin (npair zero (pMag p)).
-- ZRel p (npair zero (pMag p)):  add (fst p) (pMag p) = add zero (snd p) = snd p.
-- pMag p = add mfn (monus(snd,fst)) = monus(snd,fst) here, and the pMagFull obligation
-- (commuted) gives add (fst p) (monus(snd,fst)) = snd p.
zReconNegP : (p : NatPair) -> Eq Bool (pSign p) true -> ZRel p (npair zero (pMag p)) is
  fn (p : NatPair) (hs : Eq Bool (lte (fst p) (snd p)) true) is
    -- mfn0 : monus (fst p)(snd p) = 0
    -- Goal: add (fst p) (pMag p) = add zero (snd p)  (RHS ~> snd p).
    trans
      -- add (fst p)(pMag p) = add (fst p)(monus (snd p)(fst p))   [pMag p = add mfn msn, mfn=0]
      (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add (fst p) (add s (monus (snd p) (fst p))) end)
        (monusLteZero (fst p) (snd p) hs))
      (trans
        -- add (fst p)(add 0 (monus(snd,fst))) = add (fst p)(monus(snd,fst))  (add 0 x ~> x; refl)
        (refl (add (fst p) (monus (snd p) (fst p))))
        -- = snd p, via the commuted pMagFull obligation:
        --   pMagFull p : add (fst p)(monus(snd,fst)) = add (monus(fst,snd)) (snd p)
        --   with monus(fst,snd)=0: = add 0 (snd p) = snd p.
        (trans
          (pMagFull p)
          (trans
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is add s (snd p) end) (monusLteZero (fst p) (snd p) hs))
            (refl (snd p)))))
  end
end

zReconNeg : (z : Z) -> Eq Bool (zSign z) true -> Eq Z z (zneg (zfrom (zMag z))) is
  fn (z : Z) is
    qind NatPair ZRel (fn (w : Z) is Eq Bool (zSign w) true -> Eq Z w (zneg (zfrom (zMag w))) end)
      (fn (p : NatPair) is
        fn (hs : Eq Bool (zSign (qin NatPair ZRel p)) true) is
          qsound NatPair ZRel p (npair zero (pMag p)) (zReconNegP p hs)
        end
      end)
      z
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- THE GENERAL INVERSE.  qinvP p = sb / a sign-normalised so the denominator is a positive
-- Nat: numerator carries the sign of a (zneg sb if a ≤ 0, else sb), denominator index is
-- magPred a (so the denominator is succ (magPred a) = zMag a = |a|, positive for a ≠ 0).
-- ============================================================================

-- the sign-selected numerator:  if (zSign a) then zneg sb else sb.
signedNum : Bool -> Z -> Z is
  fn (b : Bool) (sb : Z) is BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Z end) (zneg sb) sb b end
end

qinvP : QPair -> QPair is
  fn (p : QPair) is
    qpair (signedNum (zSign (qnum p)) (zden p)) (magPred (qnum p))
  end
end

-- qinv on a representative class (the field inverse). The zNonzero hypothesis is what the
-- field LAW consumes; the inverse itself is structurally total (magPred always returns a
-- Nat), so we expose it as qinv : QPair -> Q, with the proof carried into qmulInvR.
qinv : QPair -> Q is fn (p : QPair) is qin QPair QRel (qinvP p) end end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE CORE ℤ IDENTITY behind the field law:  a · signedNum (zSign a) sb = sb · |a|.
-- Case on b = zSign a (generalised so BoolElim computes), using the signed reconstruction
-- of a and zNegMulNeg / zmulComm.
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
signCases : (a : Z) -> (sb : Z) -> (b : Bool) -> Eq Bool (zSign a) b
   -> Eq Z (zmul a (signedNum b sb)) (zmul sb (zfrom (zMag a))) is
  fn (a : Z) (sb : Z) (b : Bool) (eb : Eq Bool (zSign a) b) is
    BoolElim (fn (x : Bool) is Eq Bool (zSign a) x -> Eq Z (zmul a (signedNum x sb)) (zmul sb (zfrom (zMag a))) end)
      -- b = true: signedNum true sb = zneg sb; a = zneg (zfrom |a|).
      (fn (e : Eq Bool (zSign a) true) is
         trans
           -- zmul a (zneg sb) = zmul (zneg (zfrom |a|)) (zneg sb)   [zReconNeg]
           (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s (zneg sb) end) (zReconNeg a e))
           (trans
             -- = zmul (zfrom |a|) sb                                [zNegMulNeg]
             (zNegMulNeg (zfrom (zMag a)) sb)
             -- = zmul sb (zfrom |a|)                                [zmulComm]
             (zmulComm (zfrom (zMag a)) sb))
       end)
      -- b = false: signedNum false sb = sb; a = zfrom |a|.
      (fn (e : Eq Bool (zSign a) false) is
         trans
           -- zmul a sb = zmul (zfrom |a|) sb                        [zReconPos]
           (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul s sb end) (zReconPos a e))
           -- = zmul sb (zfrom |a|)                                  [zmulComm]
           (zmulComm (zfrom (zMag a)) sb)
       end)
      b
      eb
  end
end

-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- THE FIELD LAW at the representative level:  QRel (qmulP p (qinvP p)) (1/1).
--   numerator obligation reduces to  zmul a (signedNum (zSign a) sb) = zden (qmulP p (qinvP p))
--   = zmul sb (zfrom (succ (magPred a))) = zmul sb (zfrom |a|)  [magPredSucc, needs a ≠ 0].
-- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qmulInvP : (p : QPair) -> zNonzero (qnum p)
   -> QRel (qmulP p (qinvP p)) (qpair zone zero) is
  fn (p : QPair) (pf : zNonzero (qnum p)) is
    -- Goal: zmul (zmul (qnum p) (signedNum (zSign (qnum p)) (zden p))) zone
    --     = zmul zone (zden (qmulP p (qinvP p))).
    trans
      -- LHS: drop the unit denominator  X · 1 = X
      (zmulOneR (zmul (qnum p) (signedNum (zSign (qnum p)) (zden p))))
      (trans
        -- X = zmul (zden p) (zfrom (zMag (qnum p)))     [signCases at b = zSign (qnum p)]
        (signCases (qnum p) (zden p) (zSign (qnum p)) (refl (zSign (qnum p))))
        (trans
          -- zfrom (zMag a) = zfrom (succ (magPred a))   [sym magPredSucc, needs a ≠ 0]
          (cong (fn (s : Z) is zmul (zden p) s end)
            (cong (fn (s : Nat) is zfrom s end) (sym (magPredSucc (qnum p) pf))))
          (trans
            -- zmul (zden p) (zfrom (succ (magPred a))) = zmul (zden p) (zden (qinvP p))
            -- = zden (qmulP p (qinvP p))                [sym qmulDenZ]
            (sym (qmulDenZ p (qinvP p)))
            -- = zmul zone (zden (qmulP …))              [sym zmulOneL]
            (sym (zmulOneL (zden (qmulP p (qinvP p))))))))
  end
end

-- THE FIELD LAW, lifted:  (qin p) · (qin p)⁻¹ = 1  for ANY nonzero numerator.  ℚ is a FIELD.
qmulInvR : (p : QPair) -> zNonzero (qnum p)
   -> Eq Q (qmul (qin QPair QRel p) (qinv p)) qone is
  fn (p : QPair) (pf : zNonzero (qnum p)) is
    qsound QPair QRel (qmulP p (qinvP p)) (qpair zone zero) (qmulInvP p pf)
  end
end

-- ============================================================================
-- SANITY — the GENERAL inverse computes on a NEGATIVE rational.
-- −2/3:  numerator −2 = qin (0, 2),  denominator index 2 (denominator succ 2 = 3).
-- ============================================================================

-- −2 : Z  and  the QPair −2/3.
zNegTwo : Z is qin NatPair ZRel (npair zero (succ (succ zero))) end
qNegTwoThirdsP : QPair is qpair zNegTwo (succ (succ zero)) end
qNegTwoThirds : Q is qin QPair QRel qNegTwoThirdsP end

-- its numerator is nonzero: zIsZero (−2) = eqNat 0 2 = false (refl), so zNonzero.
qNegTwoThirdsNZ : zNonzero (qnum qNegTwoThirdsP) is
  zIsZeroFalseNonzero zNegTwo (refl false)
end

-- the sign of −2 is true (0 ≤ 2, lte 0 2 ~> true) and its magnitude is 2 (|0 − 2| = 2),
-- both computing through the quotient — refl.
qExNegSign : Eq Bool (zSign zNegTwo) true is refl true end
qExNegMag : Eq Nat (zMag zNegTwo) (succ (succ zero)) is refl (succ (succ zero)) end

-- the inverse of −2/3 is the class of the sign-normalised representative −3/2:
-- numerator = signedNum true (zfrom 3) = zneg (zfrom 3),  denominator index = magPred (−2) = 1.
qInvNegTwoThirds : Q is qinv qNegTwoThirdsP end
qInvNegTwoThirdsRep : Q is
  qin QPair QRel (qpair (zneg (zfrom (succ (succ (succ zero))))) (succ zero))
end

-- qinv (−2/3) IS that class — refl through the quotient (the sign / magnitude / magPred all
-- compute on the concrete representative).
qExInvComputes : Eq Q (qinv qNegTwoThirdsP) qInvNegTwoThirdsRep is
  refl (qinv qNegTwoThirdsP)
end

-- THE FIELD LAW on the NEGATIVE rational:  (−2/3) · (−2/3)⁻¹ = 1.
qExInvNeg : Eq Q (qmul qNegTwoThirds (qinv qNegTwoThirdsP)) qone is
  qmulInvR qNegTwoThirdsP qNegTwoThirdsNZ
end

-- ============================================================================
-- ℚ IS NOW A FULLY VERIFIED FIELD.  The commutative-ring laws (ch113: qmulOneR,
-- qaddZero, qmulAssoc, qaddAssoc, qmulDistR + ch108 qmulComm/qaddComm) together with the
-- GENERAL multiplicative inverse qinv + the field law qmulInvR (q · q⁻¹ = 1 for ANY
-- nonzero q, sign-normalised via the ZRel-respecting magnitude zMag and sign zSign and the
-- integer negation zneg) certify (ℚ, +, ·, 0, 1, ⁻¹) a FIELD.
--
-- NEXT (M6 → ordered field / ℝ):  the ORDER on ℚ — qlt : Q -> Q -> Bool respecting QRel
-- (cross-multiply the numerators against the positive denominators, reusing lte + its
-- add-cancellation here), then the ORDERED-FIELD axioms (qlt total/transitive, translation-
-- and positive-scaling-invariance). With a verified ordered field, the next stdlib step is
-- ℝ as the CAUCHY COMPLETION of ℚ (sequences of rationals with a modulus of convergence,
-- quotiented by the "eventually within ε" relation — the SAME Quot/qsound/qlift pattern one
-- level up), giving the complete ordered field that closes the M6 numeric tower.
-- ============================================================================
